Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:01:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an hour late. I'm going to pass the, I just thought some people might put this together.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.45,0:01:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It sounds sort of academically. It starts with a syllabus, and then it goes on to a synopsis.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.79,0:01:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We could pass these out. A syllabus and a synopsis. It tells us what we're going to be talking about today,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.87,0:01:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,which I have the slightest idea, but it looks good on paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.37,0:01:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It features the academic people. Well, I did give a conference a week or two ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.21,0:01:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and a lot of people get continuing education credits, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.48,0:01:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,If any of you need continuing education credits, I have certificates of education here, good, for three credits.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.03,0:02:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Today will certainly be at least three credits. So anybody who needs any, I have these here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.41,0:02:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all signed, and we'll just put the date, and the name of the presentation is on the syllabus.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.03,0:02:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And so those who would like, you know, continuing education academic credits, we officially have them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.31,0:02:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Close for five minutes early. I just want to make sure we're close for five minutes early.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.39,0:02:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we run out of them, we'll get some more made.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.22,0:02:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, what we do is, let's see what the name of it would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.74,0:02:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We have Commissioner Ashley's, which is, I feel like it's over 470, 472, 475, 480, 478, 479, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.86,0:02:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It was 770 before, but I did resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.44,0:02:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.46,0:03:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a very exciting audience to speak to.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.18,0:03:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what we always do is calibrate the level of consciousness of the audience before and after the presentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.42,0:03:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And historically, the level of consciousness of the audience usually jumps considerably.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.02,0:03:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, a group like this will jump considerably.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.56,0:03:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And the average group will jump probably about 10 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.94,0:03:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we said in the book, Power Versus Force,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.12,0:03:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the consciousness level of the average person increases by five points in a lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.84,0:03:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you can knock off 10 points in one lecture, that's two lifetimes right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.66,0:03:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That's two times you won't have to come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.94,0:03:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, I just thought that was good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.28,0:04:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we have most luxurious accommodations here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.93,0:04:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And we were greeted in the most impressive airport parking lot I've ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.31,0:04:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,In my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.01,0:04:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It went on for miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.51,0:04:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We traveled.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.51,0:04:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,She had a compass with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.51,0:04:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It was phenomenal, I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.51,0:04:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It took great courage, great courage and stamina to, brave that to come and find us and bring us here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.51,0:04:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And here we are in California.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.15,0:04:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you see, we have to set up for transparency and the transparency of course is sitting home on my desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.50,0:04:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.60,0:04:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.79,0:04:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.81,0:04:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.87,0:04:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.91,0:04:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.95,0:04:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.99,0:04:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.03,0:04:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.25,0:04:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.31,0:04:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.39,0:04:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.43,0:04:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.53,0:04:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.25,0:04:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So, today we will just have to speak from truth and that will have to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.37,0:04:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And the other thing we'll do that's different in this lecture is we'll stay right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.13,0:05:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll stay right now at all times.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.99,0:05:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And I want you to notice that we will not let the past catch up with us or the future elude us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.83,0:05:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Because most people spend all their time trying to catch the past, the future before it escapes them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.90,0:05:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and holding off the past so it won't catch up with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.41,0:05:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So the only safe place to be at any time is right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.27,0:05:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And so throughout this lecture we'll say right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.74,0:05:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So everybody will be safe from the past and safe from the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.91,0:05:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And the reason for saying that is because everyone looks to see,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.17,0:05:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, where is enlightenment and when is it going to happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.27,0:05:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And everybody looks into the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.71,0:05:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Or they look into the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.29,0:05:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They say it's either my karma from the past
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.63,0:05:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,or it's something that I will evolve into sometime in the future
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.31,0:05:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,or some future lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.30,0:06:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And the fact is it's found in the immediate moment of now,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.64,0:06:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in the split second, in the split second between two thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.34,0:06:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,which is what the Buddha said.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.68,0:06:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And he was correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.94,0:06:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It was in the same place he said it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.60,0:06:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, it was still there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.96,0:06:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It never moved in all these thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.96,0:06:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's right here right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.91,0:06:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And how to stay on the edge of now is partly what we'll be talking about today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.98,0:06:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So the syllabus says that we will be talking about who the speaker is
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.80,0:06:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and various subjects.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.68,0:06:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We will cover the levels of consciousness and their inference.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.73,0:06:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be talking about the different situations,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.48,0:06:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,between linear and non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.25,0:06:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So to make everything that I say simple,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.21,0:06:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll start out from the most difficult and obscure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.89,0:07:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That will make the rest simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.13,0:07:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is that we have two ways of experiencing reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.33,0:07:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,One is in the linear Newtonian paradigm of reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.40,0:07:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,which has to do with form, has to do with structure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.29,0:07:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And the linear linearism,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.23,0:07:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,linear reality is discreditable in terms of advanced theoretical math and physics,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.93,0:07:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and especially of the differential calculus.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.64,0:07:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But a lot of data falls outside the realm of the predictable mathematically.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.85,0:07:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It falls outside the expected paradigm of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.59,0:07:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And our society is primarily oriented to the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.03,0:07:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Our society in America, the caliber is extremely high,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.63,0:07:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and indicates that it's the intellect,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.47,0:07:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and indicates that it's the intellect,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.05,0:07:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and indicates that it's the intellect,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.15,0:08:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that we worship as God.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.45,0:08:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Science is the, it's taken over the point,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.49,0:08:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the one that's taken by religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.51,0:08:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we look for answers, we look to the intellect,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.27,0:08:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and we look for science to come up with the answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.74,0:08:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The only difficulty with science is that,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.08,0:08:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in our level of consciousness, as you can see,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.22,0:08:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,we have our levels of consciousness here,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.98,0:08:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,a map of consciousness where everybody can just refer to it if they want.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.82,0:08:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But the reason the intellect calibrates in the 400s,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.39,0:08:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,well,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.97,0:08:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual truth in reality, you know, the reality of spiritual truth really commences formally around 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.47,0:08:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,500 is the level of love, 540 is unconditional love.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.96,0:08:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So the realm of science then takes us up really to 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.74,0:09:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If we calibrate 499, we see Einstein, Freud, Sir Isaac Newton,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.12,0:09:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,all the great scientists.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.06,0:09:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All the great geniuses of old time calibrate around 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.81,0:09:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,500 is the level of the heart, 500 is the opening of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.65,0:09:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,500 is the, really the, taking over of the non-linear dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.32,0:09:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,From 500 and up we're talking about qualities that are powerful qualities,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.92,0:09:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that cannot be measured.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.78,0:09:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Love, meaning, significance, motivation, all the things that run human beings,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.94,0:09:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,are in the non-linear, non-measurable domain,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.22,0:09:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore not within the realm of science, not describable, not measurable.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.02,0:09:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So the radical materialist, reductionist materialism,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.98,0:09:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,states that unless a thing can be weighed or measured,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.00,0:09:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,then it has no reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.36,0:10:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only a tautology, that's a popular philosophic system that says you can't measure it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.53,0:10:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a tautology,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.53,0:10:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and a philosophic system that says you can't measure it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.09,0:10:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a tautology, and a philosophic system that says you can't measure it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.39,0:10:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a tautology, and a philosophic system that says you can't measure it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.55,0:10:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a tautology, and a philosophical system, but not a reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.52,0:10:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, today we're going to say the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.36,0:10:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Today we're going to say that the measurable is a perceptual construct,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.34,0:10:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and that what's real is that which cannot be measured.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.86,0:10:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Things that make human life human, none of them are measurable.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.43,0:10:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Although we talk in language, and verbalize, and move about in a physical material world,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.62,0:10:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,human existence is really lived on the level
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.48,0:10:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,of the non-linear. From moment to moment, although you may be observing a linear reality
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.78,0:11:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,such as tables and chairs or numbers or articles in a grocery store, at every instant you're
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.11,0:11:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,really coming out of an invisible space of your own existence which has no form whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.68,0:11:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Even when you decide to vote, you just, out of your right side of your brain, you pick
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.72,0:11:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,this one. Then suddenly the left side comes in and says, the reason I picked this one
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.82,0:11:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,is this. All that is an afterthought. You didn't pick it for that reason at all. You
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.90,0:11:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,don't even know why you picked what you picked because it has to do with 10 million variables
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.36,0:11:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout all of time and throughout all of this existence and all the input of this
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.49,0:11:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,entire lifetime and all of the subtleties and interactions.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.29,0:11:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.61,0:11:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So complex that no computer could possibly calculate it. So our real existence then,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.42,0:11:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,although we deal with form, we deal with form from a space of non-form, the non-linear dimension
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.13,0:12:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,of reality. And spiritual work then is concerned with the non-dimensional, the non-dimensional
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.25,0:12:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,non-measurable. So of course what we did in the book, what we did in Power vs. Force is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.78,0:12:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,measure the immeasurable.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.82,0:12:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what was the purpose of that? The purpose of that was to try to make the obvious comprehensible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.43,0:12:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the people who are in left brain and into the world of science and logic and calibrate,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.35,0:12:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say in the 400s or below, spiritual reality is not a real reality to them. And
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.70,0:12:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the scientific people would like to say this is all fantasy, etc. But it's not. It's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.24,0:12:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.13,0:12:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not. It's not. It's not. It is not. It's not. It is not. It's not. So what we needed
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.33,0:12:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,was a means of crossing over from Newtonian paradigm of reality, measurable, scientific,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.53,0:12:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,logical, sequential world of existence to the non-linear world of spiritual reality
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.90,0:13:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and a way of making the non-spiritual world comprehensible to the intellect. So the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.73,0:13:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,whole purpose of the map of consciousness, which is on the back of page 1, is to make
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.88,0:13:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the non-life understand the idea of spiritual reality as something that is not absolutely
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.76,0:13:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,meaning in topic. So the purpose of the map of consciousness is to make the non-life stream,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.92,0:13:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,transition from the nonlinear to the linear comprehensible so that even the scientific
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.41,0:13:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,skeptic can look at it and say huh you mean to tell me there is an actual objective means
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.12,0:13:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you know verifying the existence of a nonlinear domain not only that but calibrating its low
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.44,0:13:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,relative energy its relative power so when we did the levels of consciousness we started out
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.89,0:13:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,from one to a thousand one to a thousand and then we found this out the scale came about empirically
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.16,0:14:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,we said if the existence is one existence is one logarithmic scale what would be the highest number
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.10,0:14:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,ever achieved by any living being and instead of thousand I thought well that's pretty neat
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.50,0:14:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,one to a thousand that's very cooperative so then we went back and we asked
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.86,0:14:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,we found out that that which is true makes you go strong with kinesiology and that which
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.14,0:14:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,is false makes you go weak and what was the number of that and we came up with 200 so the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.49,0:14:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,most crucial thing about the map of consciousness is that anything under 200 makes you go weak and
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.53,0:14:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,anything over 200 makes you go strong so the exciting thing was that kinesiology differentiated
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.74,0:14:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,truth from falsehood that was the most significant finding and when I studied
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.73,0:14:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,kinesiology I attended lectures by John Diamond who wrote your body doesn't lie and he's a
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.68,0:15:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,wonderful teacher he's a psychiatrist and he's in New York and John Diamond had picked up the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.72,0:15:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,kinesiologic technique from George Goodhart chiropractor I think in Detroit who had worked
