Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.53,0:29:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And in many countries it's illegal and going out of style.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.11,0:29:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the Pope says he thinks it's a poor idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.11,0:29:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And that always puzzled me,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.67,0:29:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,how the Church could hold for capital punishment
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.51,0:29:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,considering what Jesus taught about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.59,0:29:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But anyway, those are the ambiguities of human consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.00,0:30:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see the difference between,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.10,0:30:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,between force and power,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.10,0:30:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,what these things are bringing us to look at.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.10,0:30:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The name of the book which I wrote was called
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.10,0:30:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Power vs. Force.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.29,0:30:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And it compares the two different domains.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.61,0:30:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The lower consciousness levels,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.61,0:30:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the world of Newtonian logic, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.61,0:30:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The world of form is the world of force,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.61,0:30:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,which is quite a bit different than the world of power.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.15,0:30:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It has different rules, different laws,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.89,0:30:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,different ways of expressing itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.89,0:30:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,different consequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.89,0:30:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What North and South Korea were looking at was,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.37,0:30:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,only a couple of years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.53,0:30:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the likelihood of force.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.79,0:30:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Force vs. force.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.79,0:30:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If one side used force, the other would use bigger force.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.92,0:30:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So what if it ended up as an atomic war, frankly,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.92,0:31:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,ballistic missiles and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.46,0:31:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Because force always results in counter force.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.46,0:31:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This is true within the world of physics.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.46,0:31:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's also true within the psychic domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.46,0:31:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But force results in counter force.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.00,0:31:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the characteristic of force is that
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.00,0:31:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,force moves from here to there.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.00,0:31:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Force moves from here to there.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.00,0:31:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And because it moves from here to there,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.04,0:31:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it consumes energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.04,0:31:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Force sooner or later runs out
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.22,0:31:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,because it runs out of its source of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.22,0:31:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You can send only so many troops to the front
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.22,0:31:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and then pretty soon your supply line goes down
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.22,0:31:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and the spirit of the men goes down.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.22,0:31:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And no matter how victorious your army may be,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.22,0:31:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,it's only a matter of time before the Roman legions
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.22,0:31:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,would reach defeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.22,0:31:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,They lasted longer than most.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.22,0:31:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But force is then consuming of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.76,0:31:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And force exhausts itself because in its expression
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.76,0:32:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it triggers from the universe counter force.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.76,0:32:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Force requires, triggers counter force.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.92,0:32:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore it consumes endless energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.08,0:32:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we see from our annual income tax,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.08,0:32:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,it has a voracious appetite.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.08,0:32:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It eats up energy endlessly, endlessly,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.08,0:32:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to overcome obstacles
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.08,0:32:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,because it doesn't understand power.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.08,0:32:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Power, which is non-form,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.20,0:32:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,has completely opposite characteristics.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.20,0:32:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Power does not consume
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.20,0:32:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,any energy at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.40,0:32:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Power instead radiates energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.46,0:32:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So power would be like gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.46,0:32:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Gravity just stands there.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.46,0:32:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It just stands there
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.46,0:32:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and it influences everything,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.46,0:32:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,all the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.88,0:32:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,more profoundly than any other factor actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.06,0:32:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The sun just shines,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.06,0:32:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,radiates forth energy to the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.06,0:33:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Not selectively, not onto this plant
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.06,0:33:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and not on that plant,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.06,0:33:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but onto everything and everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.06,0:33:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It just radiates forth endless energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.15,0:33:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So power then is more profound.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.72,0:33:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And because it does not consume energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.72,0:33:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,it outlasts force.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.72,0:33:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,When you put power and force together,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.72,0:33:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually power wins out
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.72,0:33:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,because it doesn't need any additional supplies.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.79,0:33:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It just stands there until force runs out of ammunition
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.82,0:33:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and then falls over of itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.94,0:33:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We notice that the energy fields from 200 up then
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.94,0:33:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,are the beginning of power.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.94,0:33:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,200 down on our calibrated level there,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.32,0:33:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll see it has to do with force
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.32,0:33:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and it has to do with emotionality
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.32,0:33:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and it leads to exhaustion.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.68,0:33:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only so much fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.68,0:33:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,so much grief,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.68,0:33:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,so many tears,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.68,0:33:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,so much pridefulness,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.68,0:33:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,so much aggression
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.68,0:34:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,when you finally run out of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.41,0:34:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Once it's no longer a novelty
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.41,0:34:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and once you've gotten squeezed all the drama you can out of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.41,0:34:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,it sort of loses its appeal.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.89,0:34:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Power on the other hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.89,0:34:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,such as the most common example in human experiences,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.89,0:34:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the power of love,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.89,0:34:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,power emanates and radiates endlessly
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.89,0:34:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and it originates out of the essence of its own nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.27,0:34:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So power then is the radiation of creation expressing itself
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.27,0:34:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,in ways that influence all of life
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.51,0:34:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,without the expenditure of any energy
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.67,0:34:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and without causing any reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.67,0:34:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So power doesn't cause a reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.67,0:34:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's no counter,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.67,0:34:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no counter reaction to power
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.67,0:34:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's always counter reaction to force.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.67,0:34:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody got any questions thus far?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.58,0:35:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Were there circumstances around 1986,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.76,0:35:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,outward circumstances?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.16,0:35:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, what happened in 1986,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.16,0:35:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you see you don't know which is cause and which is effect
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.42,0:35:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and which is merely concordance,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.42,0:35:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,which brings us, we'll talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.42,0:35:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,creation versus causation and what that brings to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.46,0:35:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened at that time was
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.46,0:35:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,an evolution of consciousness that reached a point
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.46,0:35:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that was marked historically by the,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.16,0:35:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,what was it, the confluence of the something or others,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.41,0:35:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,what was it in 1986, the confluence of the?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.08,0:35:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Harmonic convergence, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.08,0:35:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Harmonic convergence was the event that marked that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.15,0:35:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It didn't cause it,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.15,0:35:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,but it was the coalition of all those forces
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.15,0:35:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,at that moment did express them
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.60,0:36:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and themselves and people everywhere
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.92,0:36:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,joined in prayer for peace
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.92,0:36:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and there was an enormous power of prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.46,0:36:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,going on at that time as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.68,0:36:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And a concordance of evolution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.68,0:36:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout time, it reached a jumping off place
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.68,0:36:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and crossed over that line unnoticed by anyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.71,0:36:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,unnoticed, nobody noticed it,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.71,0:36:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the most significant event in all of human history
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.71,0:36:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,sadly occurred without a single headline.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.96,0:36:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,All of life is different as a result.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.22,0:36:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It is so profound.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.22,0:36:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like the overall temperature of the globe
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.22,0:36:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,going up two degrees, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.22,0:36:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the children on the street don't notice it,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.22,0:36:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,but the difference in production of vegetation
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.22,0:36:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout the planet, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.22,0:36:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,runs into billions of tons of,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.22,0:36:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, the profound implication and effect
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.44,0:36:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,on all of life on the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.44,0:36:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,by even a couple of degrees shift
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.44,0:36:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,which goes, you know, generally unnoticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.64,0:37:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we had,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.64,0:37:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,it wasn't just the size of the jump from 190 to 207,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.64,0:37:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but the fact that it crossed a critical line,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.64,0:37:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that was what was critical.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.96,0:37:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So the difference between 31 degrees and 32 degrees
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.96,0:37:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is quite a bit, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.96,0:37:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,because at 31 everything turns to solid or ice
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.99,0:37:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and at 32 it turns to water,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.99,0:37:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's only one degree,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.99,0:37:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,but what a significant degree that,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.99,0:37:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and the same thing occurs at 212, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.40,0:37:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,211 is water,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.40,0:37:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,212 is steam and turns into gas,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.40,0:37:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,so that crossing over to 207 was very profound
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.66,0:37:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,because now the quality, the quality of change,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.66,0:37:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,it wasn't just a quantitative change,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.66,0:37:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it was a qualitative change.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.56,0:37:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can feel somewhat optimistic
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.04,0:37:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that the future then of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.04,0:37:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is obviously quite a bit,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.04,0:37:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,going to be quite different,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.04,0:37:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,or is already quite different
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.04,0:37:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,than it was or could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.23,0:38:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,At 190 it could not improve,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.23,0:38:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,it really couldn't do anything more
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.23,0:38:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,than what it did.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.19,0:38:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,At 207 almost anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.19,0:38:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,it can go almost anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.19,0:38:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And we will see all these changes of,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.19,0:38:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,shifts of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.19,0:38:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,now that we're aware that this is taking place,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.19,0:38:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see it in the headlines,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.19,0:38:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you didn't see it before,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.19,0:38:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you thought it was just a sequence of current events,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.51,0:38:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's not just a sequence,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.51,0:38:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you see a shift in the nature, in the tone,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.51,0:38:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and we hear people talking about the quality of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.57,0:38:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the quality of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.57,0:38:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,not only just keeping people alive longer,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.57,0:38:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.60,0:38:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,ensuring the quality of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.60,0:38:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,quality of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.99,0:38:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,HMOs are not too interested in the quality of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.99,0:38:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,but mankind is, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.28,0:38:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean individuals?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.88,0:39:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure even the frogs felt it,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.24,0:39:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,but they didn't express it, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.24,0:39:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So a lot of people felt the shift,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.24,0:39:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and they weren't sure what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.24,0:39:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and so I'm just trying to define it,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.24,0:39:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and make it rather specific,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.27,0:39:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we know what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.78,0:39:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to bring up then,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.78,0:39:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the difference between creation and causality,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.61,0:39:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,a very significant understanding,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.68,0:39:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,because from 200 down,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.68,0:39:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the world of form,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.87,0:39:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the world of force,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.87,0:39:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,you're dealing in what is termed causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.87,0:39:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The world's understanding of what makes things happen
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.32,0:39:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,within the visible domain
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.32,0:39:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is that it's like billiard balls,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.32,0:39:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,A hits B hits C,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.32,0:39:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and you have a sequence of causalities,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.32,0:39:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and this explains the phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.44,0:39:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that are witnessed within the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.44,0:39:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,When we look at the world from a different viewpoint,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.79,0:39:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,from the non-linear,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.79,0:40:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll see that no such a thing happens at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.79,0:40:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, sequence is only a phenomenon
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.79,0:40:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,in human consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.79,0:40:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,it has no objective reality of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.08,0:40:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Sequence is a sequence of perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.08,0:40:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You see this, then you see that,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.08,0:40:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,then you see that,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.08,0:40:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,just because you saw them sequentially,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.08,0:40:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't mean that it's happening sequentially.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.24,0:40:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole idea that there's a happening out there
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.24,0:40:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is an invention within the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.24,0:40:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The only place a happening occurs
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.24,0:40:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is in your own mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.24,0:40:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,In the world there isn't such a thing as a happening or an event.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.10,0:40:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You can witness anything out there and say,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.10,0:40:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,start now, end now,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.10,0:40:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,so that's an event.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.10,0:40:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You can make the event this long,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.10,0:40:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you can make the event this long,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.10,0:40:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,it's when you say it starts,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.10,0:40:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's when you say it stops.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.10,0:40:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the world there is no events.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.61,0:40:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,There is nothing really that requires
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.61,0:40:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,an explanation of causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.61,0:40:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Because what you're witnessing
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.61,0:40:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is the sequence of revelation.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.61,0:40:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're really saying is creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.61,0:41:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The common argument,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.82,0:41:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, the creationist versus the evolutionist.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.82,0:41:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're seeing,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.88,0:41:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,what's actually being seen
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.88,0:41:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is the way creation comes about, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.68,0:41:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Power starts at the top
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.00,0:41:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it radiates down sort of
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.00,0:41:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,like a series of step-down transitions
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.41,0:41:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and transformers has become the used example.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.76,0:41:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,From the unmanifest,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.89,0:41:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,invisible domain,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.05,0:41:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in which there is no form,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.28,0:41:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is the onus
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.84,0:41:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which all of creation occurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.84,0:41:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the unmanifest comes the manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.84,0:41:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The power of the unmanifest is infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.84,0:41:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The power of the unmanifest is innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.96,0:41:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Even within the domain of advanced theoretical physics
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.96,0:41:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we know that
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.96,0:42:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the amount of potential power
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.56,0:42:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,in one cubic inch of space
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.56,0:42:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is equivalent to the entire mass of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.72,0:42:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,In any cubic inch of invisible space
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.72,0:42:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,potential energy, the power,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.59,0:42:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is greater than the equivalence
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.59,0:42:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,of the mass of the entire universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.59,0:42:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That's one cubic inch.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.36,0:42:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's a quarter of an inch.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.00,0:42:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The understanding of this then is
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.08,0:42:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that the power of the unmanifest,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.08,0:42:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is beyond form,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.08,0:42:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that out of which form arises,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.08,0:42:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,is infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.08,0:42:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.08,0:42:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Unending.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.24,0:42:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the unmanifest arises the manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.52,0:42:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We observe that in,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.70,0:42:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,we observe that in meditation
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.47,0:42:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,where you notice
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.47,0:42:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,if you start
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.82,0:43:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,asking yourself what is it that's witnessing,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.82,0:43:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,what is it that's observing,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.82,0:43:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you go through the various layers of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.82,0:43:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,until finally you get to awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.82,0:43:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of the self.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.56,0:43:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The interesting thing is
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.56,0:43:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you go higher and higher in your meditation
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.56,0:43:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is that you'll notice
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.56,0:43:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that the levels are impersonal.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.56,0:43:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is witnessing,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.91,0:43:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the content of your thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.91,0:43:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,or your feelingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.91,0:43:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,is self-existent.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.29,0:43:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not a personal you at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.29,0:43:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And you find that out of habit
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.39,0:43:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you've called it me,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.48,0:43:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but when you examine it
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.48,0:43:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize it's not really a me
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.48,0:43:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,any more than protoplasm is a me.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.48,0:43:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you'd say,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.48,0:43:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,theoretically this is me,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.48,0:43:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and if I pinch it, it feels like me,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.48,0:43:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but actually it's not me
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.48,0:43:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,because if I take it off and throw it away
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.48,0:43:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't lost any me at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.48,0:43:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm still the same me, so.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.35,0:43:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Then,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.35,0:43:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the argument between
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.20,0:43:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.62,0:43:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and creation is a fallacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.62,0:43:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, they're one and the same thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.62,0:44:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.32,0:44:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,because evolution is nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.32,0:44:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,except the way in which
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.42,0:44:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,creation manifests itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.42,0:44:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if there is creation at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.90,0:44:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,then
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.03,0:44:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,it is a continuous ongoing event,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.03,0:44:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,a continuous ongoing event.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.03,0:44:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,To understand the nature of God
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.60,0:44:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is to realize that no such thing
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.60,0:44:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is an arbitrary moment somewhere in history.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.60,0:44:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Did God suddenly roll the dice
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.60,0:44:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and then go off to retire, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.60,0:44:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is the common viewpoint, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.62,0:44:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that which is infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.62,0:44:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and that which is forever
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.62,0:44:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and that which is beyond form
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.42,0:44:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is its nature to continuously manifest creation,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.42,0:44:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and as we see the unfolding of creation
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.42,0:44:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,we think that's time
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.42,0:44:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and we think that's evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.87,0:44:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolution then occurs on the level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.87,0:44:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and we see the little animals and
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.87,0:44:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,plants and people manifesting
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.87,0:44:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,in what we call time
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.87,0:44:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's the way
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.90,0:45:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the universe is created.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.90,0:45:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, creation is continuous and ongoing,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.90,0:45:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,never ending.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.79,0:45:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.65,0:45:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The person says,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.65,0:45:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,how can I know the existence of God?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.00,0:45:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.12,0:45:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,God is that
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.12,0:45:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which existence arises.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.12,0:45:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the very fact that anything or everyone has existence
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.15,0:45:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is the creation of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.15,0:45:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,creation of God
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.15,0:45:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is existence itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.72,0:45:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we don't find
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.92,0:45:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,happiness in the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.92,0:45:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,we don't find it clinging to the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.92,0:45:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We find it by focusing on this instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.65,0:45:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The joy of this instant
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.65,0:45:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is the realization,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.65,0:45:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the recognition,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.65,0:45:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.65,0:45:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the feelingness
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.65,0:45:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that it is the presence of God
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.81,0:45:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that is sustaining my existence
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.81,0:45:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,this very moment
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.81,0:45:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and the existence of everyone here.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.81,0:46:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that I am
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.72,0:46:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is proof of the existence of God
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.72,0:46:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's all you need.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.49,0:46:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,When I studied theology,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.49,0:46:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I was an atheist at the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.56,0:46:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,but I got a straight A in theology
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.56,0:46:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.61,0:46:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.61,0:46:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the arguments for God's existence
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.61,0:46:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,really blew my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.61,0:46:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I said,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.61,0:46:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that wouldn't make an atheist out of anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.61,0:46:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Based on first cause, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.74,0:46:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what they're talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.80,0:46:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is how the mind thinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.80,0:46:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not talking about God at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.80,0:46:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,To the mind, that would seem
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.80,0:46:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that all causes must have a first cause
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.80,0:46:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and the prime cause would then be God.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.80,0:46:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But you see how that's really just
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.80,0:46:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,poking around in the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.80,0:46:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You're circling around in the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.80,0:46:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you calibrate the energy fuel of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.09,0:46:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I would say it's in the low 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.09,0:46:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,In the low 400s, people are so
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.09,0:46:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,enamored of the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.09,0:46:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that they can think now,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.09,0:47:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that they try to think,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.09,0:47:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,use thinkingness and logic
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.09,0:47:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to answer everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.09,0:47:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We have politically correct answers to everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.09,0:47:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,This comes out of the low 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.09,0:47:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It says, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.09,0:47:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,we think of a corresponding formula,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.09,0:47:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,get everybody behind it,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.09,0:47:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,it'll solve problems,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.09,0:47:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll pass a law against it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.09,0:47:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.09,0:47:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the way to stop something
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.09,0:47:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is to pass a law against it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.09,0:47:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day in the paper,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.09,0:47:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,there should be a law against something.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.09,0:47:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Pass a law against it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.09,0:47:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you've cured it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.09,0:47:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.09,0:47:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.09,0:47:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.09,0:47:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the low 400s are enamored
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.09,0:47:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,of thinkingness and the intellect
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.09,0:47:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and get carried away with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.22,0:47:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And they write most of our laws,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.22,0:47:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and they write legislation,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.38,0:47:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and all these things that sound so erudite.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.38,0:47:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Except they have a hidden downside,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.99,0:47:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and then once you put them into operation,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.99,0:47:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,you find the downside is worse than the upside was.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.99,0:47:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll give welfare to all the mothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.05,0:47:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.05,0:47:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but the thing is that they put in there,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.05,0:47:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,so long as there's not a man in the house,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.05,0:47:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,well,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.05,0:48:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,what happened as soon as they had welfare?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.24,0:48:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And if there's no man in the house,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.24,0:48:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,all the men left.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.24,0:48:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And the inner city,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.24,0:48:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,there wasn't no fathers anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.24,0:48:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should they be?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.24,0:48:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If she yee-yanks around,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.24,0:48:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no money.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.24,0:48:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.24,0:48:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the unseen downside comes around
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.24,0:48:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to kick out the good of the upside.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.24,0:48:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And so,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.24,0:48:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the intellect is limited
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.24,0:48:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in what it can accomplish in society.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.24,0:48:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.44,0:48:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,we talked about creation
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.44,0:48:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and its contrast with evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.44,0:48:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.44,0:48:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,creation,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.44,0:48:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.68,0:48:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a very complex thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.68,0:48:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a very complex thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.80,0:48:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a very complex thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.80,0:48:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a very complex thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.80,0:48:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a very complex thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.80,0:48:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a very complex thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.22,0:48:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a very complex thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.22,0:48:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.44,0:48:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,creation comes out of the essence of,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.44,0:48:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.66,0:48:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.66,0:48:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,as a perfect expression of its own essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.66,0:48:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.66,0:48:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no need for anything to cause anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.66,0:48:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything in the universe gives forth a radiation,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.72,0:48:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,a vibration,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.72,0:48:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,an energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.72,0:48:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that is characteristic,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.36,0:48:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,individual,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.36,0:48:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and unique.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.46,0:48:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything in the universe sets forth an energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.46,0:48:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and a vibration.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.46,0:49:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Throughout all of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.49,0:49:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is a vibration.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.97,0:49:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.97,0:49:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the calibrated levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.97,0:49:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,are really the levels
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.97,0:49:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,at which these vibrational fields
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.97,0:49:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,tend to congregate.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.97,0:49:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They tend to congregate.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.04,0:49:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.29,0:49:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,using chaos theory,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.29,0:49:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,non-linear dynamics,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.29,0:49:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,says that within what appears to be chaotic,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.29,0:49:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,there is really a hidden inner attractor field.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.74,0:49:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Within what appears to be a chaotic flight of birds,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.74,0:49:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,for instance,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.74,0:49:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,there is
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.74,0:49:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,an energy field,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.00,0:49:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can actually map out that energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.00,0:49:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and draw it as a design,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.00,0:49:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that the birds,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.25,0:49:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,when you see them moving around,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.25,0:49:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you see these huge flocks that all feel in unison like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.25,0:49:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,or you see them fish underwater.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.25,0:49:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Millions of fish all turn in unison.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.89,0:49:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Within the left brain of logic,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.89,0:49:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a presumption that all these fish are somehow looking at each other
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.89,0:50:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and keeping two and a half inches from each other
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.89,0:50:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and staying in line like a bunch of
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.89,0:50:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,airplanes out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.89,0:50:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.89,0:50:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,where the guys are looking at their instruments,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.89,0:50:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.89,0:50:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,hey,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.89,0:50:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Joe,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.89,0:50:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you're getting a quarter of an inch too close to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.89,0:50:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You can hear all these little fish
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.89,0:50:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and little birds and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.72,0:50:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Now,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.72,0:50:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the minute you look at it,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.72,0:50:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize there's some kind of hidden,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.72,0:50:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you can actually see,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.72,0:50:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the hidden energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.72,0:50:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in like an invisible attractor field,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.72,0:50:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's shaped like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.72,0:50:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and each one,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.72,0:50:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,each one singly is following that pattern
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.72,0:50:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,within their own mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.72,0:50:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one of them
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.72,0:50:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is singly following,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.72,0:50:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,within their mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.72,0:50:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.72,0:50:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't even know what the other one's over there doing,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.72,0:50:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,surprisingly.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.72,0:50:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one is being led by this organization
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.20,0:50:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of this intrinsic energy field,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.20,0:50:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,which in itself is extremely beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.20,0:50:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.20,0:50:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see the field itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.20,0:50:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to design it and project it,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.20,0:50:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and in graphics,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.27,0:50:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you would see the beauty of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.27,0:51:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And not only are dynamics and chaos there,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.68,0:51:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,these are called attractors,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.68,0:51:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,hidden attractor fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.68,0:51:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It was first discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.12,0:51:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,by Lorenz who discovered it
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.12,0:51:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,when he advanced computers,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.25,0:51:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,allowed Lorenz to examine
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.25,0:51:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the history of weather
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.26,0:51:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,over a great expanse of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.26,0:51:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And weather had never been predictable.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.26,0:51:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not within the predictable.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.26,0:51:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot use a computer
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.74,0:51:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and tell us what the weather's going to be next week.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.38,0:51:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But he found that
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.38,0:51:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,by organizing all this data
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.60,0:51:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,over the centuries,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.60,0:51:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that there was within it
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.66,0:51:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,a pattern that revealed
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.66,0:51:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that there was an organizational
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.76,0:51:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,hub, you might say,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.82,0:51:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,emanating forth as the changing
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.82,0:51:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,weather from century to century.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.62,0:52:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And he got a computer graphic of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.62,0:52:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's called Lorenz's Butterfly,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.62,0:52:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,very, very famous,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.62,0:52:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Lorenz's Butterfly.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.91,0:52:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And it looks something like a butterfly.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.91,0:52:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was the organizational field behind
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.91,0:52:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,weather over the centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.32,0:52:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can see the same pattern
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.32,0:52:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,when you see on TV
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.32,0:52:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,these beautiful migrations
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.39,0:52:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,of birds wheeling about
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.39,0:52:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,or the fish under the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.61,0:52:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So there you see an energy pattern
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.61,0:52:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,hidden from sight,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.61,0:52:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,revealed by their movement,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.61,0:52:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but it doesn't exist in a measurable domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.80,0:52:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't go out there
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.80,0:52:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and with a yardstick
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.80,0:52:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,find this invisible pattern
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.80,0:52:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and measure it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.80,0:52:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So it decides it didn't really exist,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.02,0:52:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that there was no organizational pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.02,0:52:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,These calibrated levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.08,0:52:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,then are really,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.27,0:52:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,what we've tuned in on is that
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.27,0:52:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,with the energy field of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.97,0:52:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to which man is subject
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.97,0:52:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and participates,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.97,0:52:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,there is hidden energy fields
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.97,0:53:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,which tend to dominate that field.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.97,0:53:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Our consciousness tends to be dominated by,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.80,0:53:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,it becomes influenced,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.31,0:53:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,extremely influenced
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.31,0:53:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,by the energy fields to which we subscribe.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.00,0:53:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So once you subscribe
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.00,0:53:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to a certain energy field,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.00,0:53:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you're really asking
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.13,0:53:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that energy field to come in
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.13,0:53:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and dominate your consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.13,0:53:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And you now
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.03,0:53:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,will feel a certain allegiance
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.03,0:53:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to these types of attitudes.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.03,0:53:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.47,0:53:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,these various energy fields
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.47,0:53:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and identify them as typical
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.69,0:53:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,social attitudes,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.69,0:53:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,vocational proclivities,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.69,0:53:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,even crime rates,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.69,0:53:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,likelihood of various health phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.82,0:53:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they're characteristic
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.82,0:53:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,of certain energy fields
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.82,0:54:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and certainly energy levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.48,0:54:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The most critical one to know about
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.48,0:54:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is over or under 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.48,0:54:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to show you kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.48,0:54:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm sure everybody here is familiar with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.48,0:54:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody here has experienced it?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.48,0:54:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody here experienced kinesiology?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.48,0:54:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,How many have not?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.64,0:54:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,How many have not?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.64,0:54:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's put it that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.64,0:54:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.64,0:54:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We will do a very brief exercise
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.64,0:54:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in which we demonstrate the basics of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.64,0:54:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.64,0:54:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,what these energy fields then tell us
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.64,0:54:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is what can be expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.64,0:54:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,More significantly,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.64,0:54:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,it tells us what is that level of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.86,0:54:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So mankind has a great dilemma
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.86,0:54:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout all of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.86,0:54:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't know the difference between truth
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.86,0:54:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and he doesn't know the difference
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.86,0:54:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,between truth and falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.86,0:54:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And he has no means of discerning it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.86,0:54:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The entire legal system
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.86,0:54:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is set upon man's ignorance, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.86,0:54:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you need 12 people
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.86,0:54:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to decide what the truth is?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.89,0:54:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can't decide truth
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.89,0:54:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,by voting for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.89,0:54:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.89,0:54:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.89,0:55:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what a ridiculous system, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.89,0:55:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.63,0:55:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So mankind has had a terrible time
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.63,0:55:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,killing each other
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.63,0:55:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and excommunicating people
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.63,0:55:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,for old Galileo.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.63,0:55:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It took the Church almost 500 years
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.63,0:55:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.72,0:55:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,okay, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.72,0:55:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I was very pleased
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.72,0:55:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,when Galileo got off the hook.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.72,0:55:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I was really,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.72,0:55:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,for a while,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.72,0:55:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I really had a problem
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.72,0:55:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,with the Church, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.72,0:55:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,because I thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.72,0:55:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,geez, it took you 500 years?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.72,0:55:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, I mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.72,0:55:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,what's 450 years?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.72,0:55:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,How did it get off the track,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.72,0:55:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.72,0:55:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, poor old Galileo
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.72,0:55:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,finally got off the hook.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.72,0:55:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy, I felt better.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.72,0:55:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I was scared to write about
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.72,0:55:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,some of the things
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.72,0:55:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I wrote about God.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.72,0:55:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Look what happened to Galileo.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.72,0:55:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He was only talking about planets, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.72,0:55:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, here you're talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.72,0:55:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,truth throughout all of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.72,0:55:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you could be right.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.72,0:55:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'm glad the Church
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.72,0:55:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,has given up frying people
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.72,0:56:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,so now I can publish the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.04,0:56:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it is a sharp razor.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.04,0:56:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a razor's edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.04,0:56:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth or falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.04,0:56:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,first time in mankind's history,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.04,0:56:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind has had to face this.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.84,0:56:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,First time man has ever had to face
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.84,0:56:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that man cannot tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.84,0:56:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That is so frightening
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.84,0:56:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that very few people
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.84,0:56:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,have really picked up
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.84,0:56:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the significance of this book at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.84,0:56:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,A group of leaders did
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.84,0:56:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and they invited me to a certain country
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.84,0:56:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,where she and I played quite a role
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.84,0:56:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,in shifting the whole paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.03,0:56:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But mostly people don't get
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.03,0:56:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,what it's about.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.03,0:56:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can tell the truth or falsehood
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.03,0:56:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,of anything within an instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.03,0:56:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The interesting thing is that
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.06,0:56:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you can tell the level of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.06,0:56:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I had at home the,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.06,0:56:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,collected the great books
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.06,0:56:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.06,0:56:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a wonderful find.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.96,0:56:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I came across them.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.96,0:56:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It used to cost me 500 bucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.96,0:56:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great book.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.56,0:56:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great book.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.56,0:56:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great book.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.56,0:56:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great book.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.56,0:56:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great book.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.56,0:56:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great book.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.60,0:56:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great book.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.60,0:56:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great book.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.60,0:56:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great book.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.98,0:56:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And published in 1933,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.98,0:56:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,University of Chicago,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.98,0:57:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, goes through Descartes and Kant
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.04,0:57:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the great thinkers
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.04,0:57:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout all of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.04,0:57:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's a wonderful collection.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.04,0:57:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The greatest thinkers of the
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.27,0:57:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Western world throughout all of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.72,0:57:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The last one in the series,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.72,0:57:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I think, is Freud.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.72,0:57:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And anyway, all of this erudition
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.72,0:57:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and it is fascinating and,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.09,0:57:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, when I was a kid
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.31,0:57:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I was into reading Plato
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.31,0:57:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and stuff while other kids
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.53,0:57:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,would go to school
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.53,0:57:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,but all the great thinkers
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.53,0:57:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout the time
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.53,0:57:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and things, think of all of them. Anyway, being a misfit, I
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.94,0:57:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,be sitting home reading Plato and Socrates and stuff. Anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.94,0:57:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,all this dissertation throughout the centuries has all been about
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.98,0:57:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,one single thing. How do you tell the truth from falsehood? That's all it's about.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.28,0:57:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All this collection of the greatest thinking of all the great thinkers of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.94,0:57:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,are all dealing, nor have they even solved, how do you tell
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.19,0:58:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth from falsehood? Well, to us it's a snap, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.15,0:58:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we have this wondrous chart here in front of us
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.32,0:58:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,which they did not have. And what this chart really says
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.51,0:58:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is truth is what you think it is within certain parameters.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.47,0:58:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth is not that truth is relative, it's that truth is
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.83,0:58:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,perceptualized completely differently depending on a level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.31,0:58:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What is truth? That one level of consciousness is ridiculous
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.37,0:58:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,at another. If a person's consciousness is at a
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.36,0:58:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,very rudimentary level,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.28,0:58:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to teach them that killing people is wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.23,0:58:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you do it, we will electrocute you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.55,0:58:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That didn't make sense, did it? Well, if you do, we will put you in prison forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.60,0:58:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't want to be free, we'll kill you until you want to be free, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.80,0:59:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Bigger, better bombs. Anyway, truth is relative and it depends on context.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.60,0:59:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That's never been said before.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.58,0:59:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no such thing as truth without delineation of context.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.74,0:59:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything that passes as truth is fallacious if it's missing the context.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.84,0:59:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And there you have the endless spin put on truth throughout history.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.84,0:59:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't define context, anybody can say anything and reframe it in some context as truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.25,0:59:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And prove it as truth within that context.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.25,0:59:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So unless you delineate context then,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.40,0:59:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.40,0:59:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,any claim to truth is, uh, fallacious.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.40,0:59:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we have the various levels of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.66,0:59:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So we say, um, let's just do a few things, uh, for fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.69,0:59:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we'll do a few things for fun. Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.46,0:59:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We said, first of all, the critical line is 200. 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.46,1:00:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is above 200 is concordant with love.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.46,1:00:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is below 200 is not concordant with love.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.46,1:00:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, people below 200 are repulsed by love.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.46,1:00:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,All the politically correct do-gooders out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.68,1:00:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we should just love them and they'll get better.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.68,1:00:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that people below 200 are repulsed by love.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.68,1:00:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nauseating.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.00,1:00:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Please leave us alone.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.32,1:00:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Disgust.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.48,1:00:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys, the people under 200 are disgusted by loving, understanding, wonderful, compassionate approaches?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.48,1:00:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,They think it's stupid.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.24,1:00:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,They've told me so.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.24,1:00:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm chief of staff at a presidential residence.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.54,1:00:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Treatment center with 54 teenage girls.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.73,1:00:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of whom are really quite committed to negativity.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.94,1:01:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a wonderful, kind, clean, it's a marvelous place.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.94,1:01:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a dream come true.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.97,1:01:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll say to a kid who just came in from Black Canyon jail.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.97,1:01:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So, how do you like it here?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.04,1:01:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,She goes,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.68,1:01:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. I guess the food wasn't so good.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.68,1:01:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the attitude is, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.60,1:01:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see, that which is negative views love as an enemy.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.60,1:01:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh-ho.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.02,1:01:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything under 200, then, views love as the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.02,1:01:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.02,1:01:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you understand? You're the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.02,1:01:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a person ask about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.11,1:01:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we just said it's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.75,1:01:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We check ourself all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.75,1:01:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of times something comes out original and say,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.75,1:01:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, that's wild something.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.75,1:01:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,How so? Okay, good.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.19,1:01:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.19,1:01:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,everything that we study,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.19,1:02:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,everything that we believe in,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.19,1:02:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,every teacher that we follow should be calibrated.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.19,1:02:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You should know the level of truth in which the person is speaking.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.19,1:02:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, to make sure that they're legitimate, over 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.19,1:02:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And to give you an idea of what level of reality,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.02,1:02:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,from what level of reality are they speaking,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.02,1:02:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you know what it is you're listening to.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.02,1:02:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So much of spiritual confusion in the spiritual community
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.15,1:02:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is due to mixing levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.15,1:02:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,New mixing levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.15,1:02:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,New mixing levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.15,1:02:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Some gurus said this, and they quoted out of context.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.34,1:02:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because it's out of context,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.34,1:02:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and you don't know who is,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.34,1:02:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,why it was said to whom, and for what reason,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.34,1:02:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and in what context of truth you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.23,1:02:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we advise everybody to do
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.64,1:02:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is to check out the level of truth of
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.64,1:02:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the writer, the speaker, the course.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.64,1:02:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't accept anything on faith.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.56,1:02:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.56,1:02:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should you not accept anything on faith?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.56,1:03:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if mankind was onto the truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.56,1:03:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,all these centuries,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.56,1:03:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,our life would be totally different, wouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.56,1:03:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There wouldn't have been any World War II or World War I.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.56,1:03:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There wouldn't be any plague.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.56,1:03:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,There wouldn't be AIDS all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.63,1:03:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,There wouldn't have been taxes rising.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.63,1:03:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,All this negativity prevails
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.95,1:03:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,because nobody checked out the level of truth of the speaker.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.95,1:03:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,If you checked out Adolf Hitler,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.17,1:03:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,it wouldn't have lasted too long.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.17,1:03:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall we give up our entire life and serve this furor?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.17,1:03:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You make sure I don't go weak, for God's sake.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.17,1:03:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Rip you off.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.17,1:03:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He ripped off the whole country, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.17,1:03:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He ripped off the whole economy,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.30,1:03:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole generation.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.30,1:03:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Wiped out all the young people.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.30,1:03:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Corrupted all their morals.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.30,1:03:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Destroyed their country.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.40,1:03:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Destroyed everything but beauty.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.88,1:03:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Brought about the destruction of the Cathedrals of Cologne.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.88,1:03:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.11,1:03:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Picture something or someone you love.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.11,1:03:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Not picture something you don't love.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.70,1:04:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the basic demonstration.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.15,1:04:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,People say they've studied this over and over.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.15,1:04:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,They can't get it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.15,1:04:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only about 18 seconds to get how to look at ideology.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.15,1:04:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I watched Dr. Diamond do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.15,1:04:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, true.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.15,1:04:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,False.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.15,1:04:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What more is there to know?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.24,1:04:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to really know anything more.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.24,1:04:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very simple.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.08,1:04:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The basic mechanism, however, is not all that simple.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.08,1:04:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Because Diamond didn't get it,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.08,1:04:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and neither did anybody,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.36,1:04:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,until we saw that what we're touching into
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.36,1:04:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,is not local causality, but non-local.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.62,1:04:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness is non-local.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.00,1:04:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What we're tapping into
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.00,1:04:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is the capacity of non-local consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.00,1:04:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to recognize truth from falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.00,1:04:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to recognize love from non-love.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.00,1:04:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The Course in Miracles, I think, as I said in the book,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.85,1:04:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,is most of the people here in the Course in Miracles?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.85,1:04:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.85,1:04:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.88,1:04:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.88,1:05:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Course in Miracles itself calibrates at 600.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.43,1:05:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if it still does.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.94,1:05:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Course in Miracles, we have permission to ask, resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.94,1:05:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates at 600, resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.10,1:05:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates at 610, resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.42,1:05:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates precisely at 600.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.74,1:05:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.74,1:05:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Very significant.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.54,1:05:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,See, to know the Course in Miracles calibrates at 600
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.67,1:05:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,gives you a whole different orientation
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.67,1:05:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of what the Course in Miracles is,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.67,1:05:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,what it's for,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.67,1:05:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,where it fits into the overall level of truth
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.83,1:05:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,as it's been expressed throughout the history of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.83,1:05:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,600, curiously, is the same level,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.98,1:05:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,same as the level of truth in kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.98,1:05:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Kinesiology, if you ask,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.30,1:05:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the level of reliability of truth in kinesiology,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.30,1:05:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,it says 600.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.30,1:05:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.30,1:05:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Course in Miracles is at 600.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.43,1:05:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Before I did it with Course in Miracles,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.52,1:05:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in Lewis, enlightenment begins at 600.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.52,1:05:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And 600, then, is the transition
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.52,1:05:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,from form to non-form,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.52,1:05:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,from the linear to the non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.52,1:06:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Once a person reaches 600,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.31,1:06:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,in our society, we say they're enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.60,1:06:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The chance is one in less than 10 million,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.60,1:06:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but it does occur.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.60,1:06:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,When it does, it's usually recorded in history
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.72,1:06:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's unusual.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.72,1:06:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,However, a lot of people, when they hit 600,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.62,1:06:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,just blitz out and leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.62,1:06:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody rears them.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.62,1:06:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody rears them.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.70,1:06:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole world wants you to resume this body
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.70,1:06:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and continue on with this pageant here.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.20,1:06:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And it doesn't seem very attractive to do, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.48,1:06:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you still have something,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.48,1:06:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're not at 1,000, you're only at 600,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.61,1:06:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you're still vulnerable to love.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.64,1:06:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And out of love,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.64,1:06:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you may decide to come back into the body and resume.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.00,1:06:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And so that's attractive.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.00,1:06:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to let go of it and get over it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.92,1:06:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So we want to calibrate
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.92,1:06:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the level of truth of everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.21,1:07:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,In the book Power Versus Force,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.21,1:07:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,we calibrated every chapter.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.21,1:07:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We calibrated the book as a whole, every chapter.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.21,1:07:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We went over every page, every paragraph, every sentence.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.34,1:07:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Examined the entire book using kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.34,1:07:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Is everything on this page correct?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.60,1:07:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Is everything on this page correct?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.63,1:07:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We found we didn't find one error.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.63,1:07:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We did find one error.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.63,1:07:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And we said, is there anything out in this chapter?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.63,1:07:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They said yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.63,1:07:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we went page by page.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.92,1:07:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there something on this page?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.92,1:07:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.92,1:07:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We got the page was on.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.92,1:07:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it in the top half of the page?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.92,1:07:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Bottom of the top half of the page.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.92,1:07:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it this paragraph?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.92,1:07:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.92,1:07:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Second sentence?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.92,1:07:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,First sentence?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.92,1:07:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I got the word.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.92,1:07:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It was John Lennon.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.92,1:07:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We took John Lennon out of the sentence,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.92,1:07:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it was perfect.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.92,1:07:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.23,1:07:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the truth are we talking about now?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.70,1:07:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so right now we're talking at 750.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.70,1:07:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, we calibrate what we are saying
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.70,1:07:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,from moment to moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.80,1:07:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The kind of material, the consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.98,1:08:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,from which this speech is being expressed, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.98,1:08:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,coming at this moment from about 750.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.01,1:08:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we go back to our levels of consciousness then,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.01,1:08:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I think when I did this we didn't know much
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.24,1:08:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,about 700 to 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.24,1:08:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we didn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.16,1:08:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We stopped at 600 because we didn't have a chance
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.16,1:08:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to check out what goes on from 600 on up.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.54,1:08:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The levels from 700 to 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.54,1:08:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what we've been working on more recently.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.54,1:08:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And the eye of the eye has to do primarily with those levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.83,1:08:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,700 to 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.83,1:08:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What are those fields of consciousness?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.08,1:08:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What do they represent?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.76,1:08:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the understanding that arises in them?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.76,1:08:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The 700s are the levels of Ramana Maharshi,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.98,1:08:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Nisargadatta Maharaj,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.98,1:08:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,great and famous saints throughout history.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.01,1:08:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And then Hoang Po.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.62,1:08:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoang Po, the 6th Patriarch.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.88,1:09:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He said 700 resists.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.88,1:09:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 700 resists.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.88,1:09:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,780 resists.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.88,1:09:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 800 resists.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.55,1:09:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He said 790 resists.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.55,1:09:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,After that Hoang Po, the transmission of mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.60,1:09:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It is 790.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.60,1:09:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There are not many people in the upper one
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.60,1:09:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,so we didn't spend much time investigating it
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.60,1:09:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,until recent times.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.83,1:09:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The most interesting thing we found about those levels
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.83,1:09:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,is that the level of the avatar is 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.83,1:09:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The human nervous system cannot tolerate
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.96,1:09:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,an energy that calibrates over 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.88,1:09:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the calibration of Buddha, Krishna, Jesus Christ, all came out at a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.56,1:09:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Their missions were somewhat different, and that's something we sort of asked recently.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.03,1:09:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The lady who read our work and called up Susan and said she was concerned about the fact
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.17,1:09:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that she felt somewhat guilty as a Catholic, adhering to a lot of Buddhist principles, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.60,1:10:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Catholicism tends to sort of have a certain rigidity about its own dogma.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.93,1:10:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So she had felt a certain conflict between Buddhism and Catholicism.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.86,1:10:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And she and Susie talked about it over the phone, and we thought about it and reflected on it
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.04,1:10:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and checked that ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.83,1:10:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was just a difference of missions.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.17,1:10:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, they both calibrated at a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.89,1:10:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So if Buddha's a thousand and Christ is a thousand, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.25,1:10:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the relationship between their teachings?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.81,1:10:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And what we got was that the purpose of the Buddha was to teach enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.39,1:10:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddha doesn't talk about salvation and the Christian sense of salvation.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.53,1:10:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha really presses towards enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.12,1:10:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus doesn't talk about enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.70,1:10:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,He talks about salvation.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.20,1:10:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That used to bother me, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.09,1:10:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, how come Jesus Christ never mentions anything about enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.43,1:11:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,when he's at a thousand the same as the Buddha?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.03,1:11:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the Buddha didn't talk about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.40,1:11:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The aim of Buddhism is not to reach a sufficient level that a savior comes and saves you
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.48,1:11:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and takes you to heaven, see.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.86,1:11:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Except there is pure land Buddhism.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.64,1:11:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Pure land Buddhism.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.92,1:11:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Pure land Buddhism.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.94,1:11:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Pure land Buddhism is sort of practical, like Jesus Christ is practical.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.16,1:11:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It sounds to me like Jesus Christ said,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.64,1:11:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the likelihood of people becoming enlightened in this lifetime is very, very slim.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.50,1:11:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of teaching people how to become enlightened,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:25.86,1:11:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,which is not going to be too attractive to them and not appeal to many
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.26,1:11:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and probably not going to happen in one in a hundred million,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.86,1:11:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,let's get practical and talk about what is achievable.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.75,1:11:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Christian principles are achievable.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.29,1:11:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And they don't take you into the five hundreds.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.11,1:11:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And from there, you obviously go to heaven.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.63,1:11:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And from heaven, you can then go the rest of the way.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.60,1:11:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So the thinking was, and it still is in many sides of Buddhism,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.07,1:11:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that the negativity of this planet is so intense
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.23,1:12:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that the likelihood of achieving enlightenment is, you know, so slim
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.27,1:12:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's not really a practical way to go for many people.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.98,1:12:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And so new land Buddhism really says practice spiritual principles
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.29,1:12:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and you will then, the Buddha,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.93,1:12:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the Buddha of salvation, Amitabha Buddha will then become your savior
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.86,1:12:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and represent you in heaven and from the new land,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.59,1:12:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,which is really one of the levels of heaven,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.97,1:12:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you can then from there shoot for enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.26,1:12:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So Jesus Christ then sounded to me like a practical person.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.16,1:12:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He's talking to, you know, the people of his time were very uneducated, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.22,1:12:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And so what he was, you know, what he,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.18,1:12:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,recommended was to avoid sin and follow virtue.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.80,1:12:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you do that, then you will qualify for salvation,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.80,1:13:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,which means starting to go to heaven.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:00.96,1:13:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's bring it up to date in modern terminology then.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.74,1:13:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Modern terminology, we'd say,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.33,1:13:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,what Jesus Christ said was avoid everything
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.29,1:13:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that calibrates below 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.29,1:13:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Simple enough, that's really all he said.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.75,1:13:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't hang out below 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.36,1:13:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are what he calls sin.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.82,1:13:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason is,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.32,1:13:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the consequences of sin are very unpleasant.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.64,1:13:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jesus did not recommend that.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.36,1:13:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,If you hang out below 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.37,1:13:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you will not be pleased with the end result, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.25,1:13:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So he was very practical.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.85,1:13:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, in his own inner self,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.36,1:13:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,he said, enlightenment is for so few.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.56,1:13:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not think of the many?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.59,1:13:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Much like Mahayana Buddhism is concerned with the many,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.94,1:13:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and Hinayana is with the few.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.32,1:13:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Christ was very practical and realized
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.32,1:13:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that only so much was possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.36,1:14:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we found out something very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.64,1:14:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's recapitulate what we found out.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:09.71,1:14:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,People who calibrate under 200 are able to get to heaven.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.86,1:14:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true or false?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:17.02,1:14:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,They're able to get to heaven.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.16,1:14:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Under 200, they're not able to get to heaven.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.70,1:14:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Under 200, you have subscribed and committed
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.70,1:14:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to that which is false, negative, destructive, evil,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.04,1:14:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,or whatever you want to call it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.04,1:14:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Under 200, unaided, one cannot get into heaven.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.49,1:14:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.84,1:14:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, why did Christ die?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.10,1:14:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He, and this suddenly came to us as an intuition, he said,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.93,1:14:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,he died to save all the people under 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.93,1:14:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ died to save the souls,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.92,1:15:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,or to give the souls of those under 200 to exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.08,1:15:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So Jesus Christ, who died for all of mankind,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.52,1:15:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,died because his energy,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.15,1:15:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,his energy field was so powerful
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.15,1:15:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that it counterbalanced the entire negativity
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.15,1:15:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of everything and everyone under 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.18,1:15:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,without whom they would end up in hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.20,1:15:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.00,1:15:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,To accept Jesus Christ as one's savior, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.00,1:15:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is crucial if your energy field is under 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.00,1:15:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 200, you don't have to be saved by Jesus
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.35,1:15:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to get to heaven.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.35,1:15:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that's so.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.82,1:15:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to over 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.41,1:15:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got enough spiritual truth within you already
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.41,1:15:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that you'll inevitably, eventually go the whole route.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.41,1:15:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Under 200, you're like a drowning person.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.31,1:15:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot save yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.50,1:16:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So Jesus Christ as savior, then, is a reality,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.62,1:16:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,which we can calibrate the truth of this very day.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.62,1:16:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He died to save the souls of all those people under 200
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.45,1:16:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,because they are so lacking in spiritual truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.45,1:16:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way they can navigate towards the light.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.45,1:16:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,To be able to be attracted by the light,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.16,1:16:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you would have to be attracted by the light.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.16,1:16:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And we just said before,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.12,1:16:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that people under 200 are not attracted by the light.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.12,1:16:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They are repelled by the light.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.12,1:16:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Repelled by the light.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.60,1:16:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So how would those people get this elevation
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.60,1:16:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,if they're repelled by spiritual truth and light?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.03,1:16:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway, I'm happy now.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.03,1:16:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ makes much more sense to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.03,1:16:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree with him totally.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.03,1:16:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it was a very practical view that he took.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.41,1:16:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And many branches of Buddhism take the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:52.41,1:16:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And we've got Hindu, Krishna,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.83,1:16:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, the ancient Vedas also say
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.83,1:17:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that this time the negativity on the planet is so extreme,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.44,1:17:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the likelihood of becoming enlightened,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.44,1:17:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not too good every 58,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.44,1:17:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,One revolution of the Zodiac, or whatever it is,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.14,1:17:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,one aeon is in the universe for 58,000 years,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.14,1:17:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,those are the only things.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.14,1:17:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.77,1:17:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the thing about studying the nature of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.77,1:17:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is you begin to have a context from which
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.77,1:17:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to understand spiritual teachings,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.77,1:17:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,a way to fit them together.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.77,1:17:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That which was once mysterious, challenging and undecipherable
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.77,1:17:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,now becomes quite logical and comprehensible.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.77,1:17:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we want to do by understanding the nature of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.84,1:17:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is to make comprehensible the incomprehensible.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.84,1:17:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It means that certain information that could not be integrated before
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.86,1:17:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,can now be integrated.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.86,1:17:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of information, once you hear it integrated,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.86,1:18:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the information itself has enormous power.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.86,1:18:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you've heard that, you're going to be a different person.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.86,1:18:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The information itself propels your consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.86,1:18:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason the levels of consciousness of people who read Power vs. Force
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.98,1:18:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,or hear a lecture like this jump afterwards
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.98,1:18:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is certain information has automatically opened new avenues in their consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.98,1:18:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see those little synapses just being happy,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.98,1:18:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,bzz, bzz, bzz, bzz, all speaking to each other and saying,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.98,1:18:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, we have to learn from you, we're many a lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.98,1:18:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, how nice, oh, how nice,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.98,1:18:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, I see, God loves me,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.98,1:18:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, oh, oh, oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.98,1:18:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the truth, wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.98,1:18:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise I wouldn't have existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.98,1:18:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If God had you, you wouldn't have existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.98,1:18:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd be squished like a bug.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.40,1:18:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Just the fact that we're here means that we're okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:48.20,1:18:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.20,1:18:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you liked to hear that this morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.43,1:18:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you were worried about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.97,1:18:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.97,1:19:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now that we know we're all okay,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.76,1:19:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we should take a break, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.76,1:19:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Exhausted ourselves with all this very interesting stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.76,1:19:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll take a shirt break.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.76,1:19:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the bust of Newark, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.08,1:19:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the bust of Newark, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.00,1:19:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I thought we'll resume as long as we're here.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.16,1:19:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as we're here.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.16,1:19:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,A couple of things I wanted to talk about today.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.16,1:19:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to explain karma because there's no,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.16,1:19:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,see, a lot of what I do, really my thrust in the world is,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.16,1:19:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to try and make comprehensible that which has not been made comprehensible throughout time,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:48.16,1:19:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,due to mistranslations, wrong words,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.16,1:19:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,mistranslations from Sanskrit,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.16,1:19:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,through Greek, through Aramaic,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.16,1:20:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,misunderstandings because teachings are heard by people who can tell they're not enlightened,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.16,1:20:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore they use the wrong word,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.16,1:20:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,they give the wrong inference.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.16,1:20:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The difference between detached and non-detached,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.16,1:20:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is profound.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.16,1:20:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And you'll see most Buddhist literature talks about detached,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.16,1:20:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and detached is different than non-detached,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.16,1:20:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,two different things.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.09,1:20:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Or the Buddha has said that there's only one sin,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.09,1:20:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.09,1:20:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's a mistranslation.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.44,1:20:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So we want to correct some of the mistranslations,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.44,1:20:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,misunderstandings, integrate the understanding of karma,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.44,1:20:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,which is one of the crossovers from Buddhism to Christianity
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.02,1:20:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that many people find difficult.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.02,1:20:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll talk about some of personal thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.66,1:20:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,experiences,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.52,1:20:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that led to some of these understandings,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.52,1:20:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,who this person is.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.48,1:20:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what it says on the syllabus here.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.68,1:20:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Familiarize and explain.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.00,1:21:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Background and qualifications of the speaker and his research,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.64,1:21:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,well that's neat.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.64,1:21:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought we'd do that a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.64,1:21:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it'll lead us into some understandings.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.15,1:21:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is speaking is consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.15,1:21:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you understand that.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.15,1:21:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Because in the linear domain,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.34,1:21:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you presume that this physicality here is the person,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.34,1:21:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and everybody presumes there's a Dr. Hawkins here
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.34,1:21:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,who's speaking and all this, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.16,1:21:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only consciousness that's speaking, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.16,1:21:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only consciousness that's speaking.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.42,1:21:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm as surprised by what goes on as anyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.42,1:21:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I'm misled by I,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.42,1:21:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm telling you from where I speak from,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.42,1:21:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't know what's going to happen either,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.42,1:21:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,or what we're even going to talk about today,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.42,1:21:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,until it happens.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.42,1:21:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Because when you live in the instant,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.64,1:21:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have any,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.25,1:21:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing's telling you what's coming up in the future,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.25,1:21:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,or what just happened in the past,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.25,1:21:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,because neither exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.25,1:21:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's always a surprise.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.99,1:22:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like riding the crest of a wig.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:02.84,1:22:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is the way to get into the instant present,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.84,1:22:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is to constantly release and let go of everything as it arises,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.84,1:22:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,like a note of music.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:09.84,1:22:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,As the note arises,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.84,1:22:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,it's already falling out of its existence, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.91,1:22:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can't stay with the music that just once was,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.91,1:22:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,nor can you live with the music that hasn't arisen yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.91,1:22:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You can only ride the note that's rising at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.39,1:22:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is a method of meditation,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.87,1:22:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,which you can do throughout the day,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.87,1:22:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but which sort of takes me out of the world considerably.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:33.70,1:22:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So one of my problems this morning is I'm not really in the world too well,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.70,1:22:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but, so...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.50,1:22:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought to give some organization,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.50,1:22:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I would just talk about my own personal experiences,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.50,1:22:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,because it says here,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.50,1:22:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,background of the speaker.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.50,1:22:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.50,1:22:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking of the background of the speaker,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.93,1:22:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,we'd have to go back some eons.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.93,1:22:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But before that,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.06,1:23:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in this lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.06,1:23:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the first conscious awareness was
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.06,1:23:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,age three.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.54,1:23:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Before three,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:07.54,1:23:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,there was nothing but void.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.18,1:23:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Three in the word,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.18,1:23:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,three was chronological in terms of the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.18,1:23:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the age of the body was three.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.18,1:23:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,All of a sudden, at age three,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.31,1:23:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,what the world says at age three,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.31,1:23:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,out of void, out of nothingness at all,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.92,1:23:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,out of nonexistence,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.27,1:23:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,there was suddenly a profound and stunning
Dialogue: 0,1:23:27.27,1:23:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,awareness of existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.27,1:23:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just suddenly,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.27,1:23:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly conscious of existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.52,1:23:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Existence as existence,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.52,1:23:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,not as existence as the physicality,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.52,1:23:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,although the physicality seemed to awake
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.52,1:23:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the awareness of existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.52,1:23:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But there was the awareness of existence as existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:46.52,1:23:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It was very intense,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.96,1:23:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was also nonverbal.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.96,1:23:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.96,1:23:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,three year old doesn't know such words.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.64,1:23:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, what a three year old notice they have on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.70,1:24:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.70,1:24:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,this consciousness was stunned by
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.70,1:24:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the sudden awareness of existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.70,1:24:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And as soon as there was the awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.70,1:24:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that I exist,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.70,1:24:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,even though I wasn't there yet,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.76,1:24:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,there was no existence as existence,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.76,1:24:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,instantly its alternative came up,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.75,1:24:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,its opposite came up,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.75,1:24:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,of nonexistence.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.75,1:24:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And instantly I was frightened.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.75,1:24:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Instantly there was the fear of nonexistence.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.23,1:24:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, out of existence arose instantly
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.23,1:24:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the duality of nonexistence.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.23,1:24:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the profound spiritual conundrum,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.87,1:24:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,koan of this lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.87,1:24:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Koan.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.57,1:24:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you pronounce it?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.47,1:24:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,C-O-H-E-N.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.47,1:24:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,No, C-O-K-A-O-A.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.47,1:24:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,K-O-A-N.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.88,1:24:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the riddle of this lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.28,1:24:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.50,1:24:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody will have to make some notes.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.50,1:25:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a couple of things we have to talk about.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.50,1:25:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to talk about positionality,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.50,1:25:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,who's going to be the secretary?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.76,1:25:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody make a note.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.76,1:25:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Positionality,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.76,1:25:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we don't want to forget that,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.76,1:25:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.17,1:25:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, because
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.17,1:25:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,what this represented also was
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.17,1:25:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,probably, you know, karmically,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.17,1:25:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,where I left off.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.17,1:25:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Where I left off as a Buddhist monk,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.17,1:25:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,a Hinayana monk.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.17,1:25:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In some lifetimes,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.17,1:25:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I would always end up as,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.17,1:25:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the ultimate reality is void.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.17,1:25:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Go out of body and experience void.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.17,1:25:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Because after all,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.17,1:25:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,if you think reality is void
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.17,1:25:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and you leave the body,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.17,1:25:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,what are you into?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.17,1:25:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You're into void.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.17,1:25:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,From that lifetime to the next,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.17,1:25:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and then suddenly you're in a new body,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.17,1:25:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,with no connecting in the astral realms.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.17,1:25:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Because as a Hinayana Buddhist,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.59,1:25:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't believe in all that stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.59,1:25:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.59,1:25:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.78,1:25:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that's what happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.78,1:25:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.78,1:25:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That is what happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.78,1:25:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,My guess is right.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.78,1:25:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That is what happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.78,1:25:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.78,1:25:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.78,1:25:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,out of voidness,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.78,1:25:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,which this,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.78,1:25:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,apparently,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.78,1:25:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Hinayana Buddhist monk felt
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.78,1:26:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,was the ultimate reality,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.78,1:26:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly there was this
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.78,1:26:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.78,1:26:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.78,1:26:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the first problem was then,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.78,1:26:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,existence versus non-existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.78,1:26:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason that's important is
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.78,1:26:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,because it represents
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.78,1:26:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the dilemma of positionality.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.77,1:26:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,See, the whole ego arises
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.77,1:26:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,out of positionality.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.51,1:26:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,All of duality arises
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.51,1:26:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,out of perception,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.51,1:26:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,out of positionality.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.51,1:26:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,All of perception
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.51,1:26:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,arises out of positionality.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:28.21,1:26:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.21,1:26:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Miracles talks about
Dialogue: 0,1:26:30.21,1:26:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the difference between
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.21,1:26:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,vision and perception.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.21,1:26:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Perception arises
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.21,1:26:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,out of taking a position.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.56,1:26:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you take
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.56,1:26:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,a position,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.56,1:26:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you've instantly created
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.56,1:26:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,a duality.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.56,1:26:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You've instantly created
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.56,1:26:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,a perceptual,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.56,1:26:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,a way of looking at things
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.49,1:26:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that's going to create
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.49,1:26:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,a right and a wrong,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:44.49,1:26:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and a good and a bad,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.49,1:26:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,a good and evil.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.49,1:26:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Positionality creates
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.20,1:26:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,a world which mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.20,1:26:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot solve.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.35,1:27:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not solvable.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.99,1:27:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you create
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.91,1:27:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,a positionality,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.91,1:27:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you create
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.00,1:27:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the unsolvable.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.00,1:27:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.00,1:27:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you can...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.00,1:27:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the Democrats
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.00,1:27:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,in their vote.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.10,1:27:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you get a dimple
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.76,1:27:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in reality,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.76,1:27:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you're screwed.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.19,1:27:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Tragically,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.19,1:27:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you're screwed.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.19,1:27:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Pregnant, dimple,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.19,1:27:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.19,1:27:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So, positionality
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.99,1:27:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,was what I was hit with.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.99,1:27:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And I didn't realize it
Dialogue: 0,1:27:31.99,1:27:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,because it was going to
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.99,1:27:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,take practically
Dialogue: 0,1:27:33.99,1:27:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,a whole lifetime
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.99,1:27:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,of spiritual evolution
Dialogue: 0,1:27:35.99,1:27:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,before I returned
Dialogue: 0,1:27:37.05,1:27:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to that same
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.05,1:27:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,positionality
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.18,1:27:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and had to resolve it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.18,1:27:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to jump
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.18,1:27:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that paradox,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.18,1:27:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the paradox
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.18,1:27:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of existence
Dialogue: 0,1:27:47.18,1:27:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,versus non-existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.18,1:27:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.40,1:27:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,when it did,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:52.40,1:27:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the level of
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.52,1:27:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:27:54.52,1:27:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,took a leap
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.52,1:27:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,because that was
Dialogue: 0,1:27:56.52,1:27:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the great
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.52,1:27:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,block.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.52,1:28:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The great block
Dialogue: 0,1:28:00.52,1:28:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,because
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.52,1:28:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,it represented
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.52,1:28:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.52,1:28:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,error
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.52,1:28:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of the ego itself
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.52,1:28:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that it
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.52,1:28:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,thinks that
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.64,1:28:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,there has to be
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.64,1:28:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,an opposite
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.64,1:28:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:10.64,1:28:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,There has to be
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.64,1:28:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,an opposite
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.64,1:28:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.98,1:28:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you take
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.33,1:28:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,a positionality.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.33,1:28:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the ego thinks
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.33,1:28:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that if something
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.33,1:28:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,is,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.33,1:28:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that brings up
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.33,1:28:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the possibility
Dialogue: 0,1:28:23.33,1:28:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,of is not.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:25.26,1:28:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.26,1:28:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,then brings up
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.26,1:28:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,its opposite.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.54,1:28:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's profound
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.54,1:28:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,because
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.54,1:28:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,people
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.54,1:28:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,other than myself
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.54,1:28:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,frankly don't
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.54,1:28:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,understand
Dialogue: 0,1:28:36.31,1:28:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.37,1:28:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,they think
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.37,1:28:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it represents
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.65,1:28:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,true versus
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.65,1:28:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,false.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.73,1:28:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I myself
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.73,1:28:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,even thought
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.73,1:28:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,so.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.73,1:28:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,In trying to explain
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.73,1:28:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,it in terms
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.73,1:28:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,of the world
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.73,1:28:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I came up
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.73,1:28:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,with the same
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.73,1:28:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,fallacy
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.53,1:28:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that the world
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.53,1:29:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,does.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:01.43,1:29:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If there's
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.43,1:29:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,a true
Dialogue: 0,1:29:03.43,1:29:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,then there must
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.72,1:29:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,be a false.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.94,1:29:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If there's
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.94,1:29:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,existence
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.94,1:29:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,then there must
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.13,1:29:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,be a false.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.13,1:29:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If there's
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.13,1:29:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,an existence
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.13,1:29:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,then there must
Dialogue: 0,1:29:16.62,1:29:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,be a false.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.62,1:29:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If there's
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.62,1:29:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,a truth
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.62,1:29:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,then there must
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.72,1:29:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,be a false.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.42,1:29:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,If there's
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.42,1:29:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,a truth
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.21,1:29:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,then there must
Dialogue: 0,1:29:31.21,1:29:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,be a false.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.24,1:29:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If there's
Dialogue: 0,1:29:33.24,1:29:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,an existence
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.24,1:29:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,then there must
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.40,1:29:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,be a false.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.40,1:29:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,In the past
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.42,1:29:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,there were
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.42,1:29:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,two kinds
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.42,1:29:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of constructions
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.42,1:29:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that have not
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.42,1:29:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,they're not
Dialogue: 0,1:29:44.58,1:29:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,based on
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.58,1:29:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,unreality.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.58,1:29:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So we said
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.58,1:29:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's commonly
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.58,1:29:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,taught
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.61,1:29:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,1:29:50.61,1:29:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when I state truth, then, consciousness recognizes truth, and her arm goes strong.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.72,1:30:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If I say something that is not true, which is different than false, the absence of truth
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.76,1:30:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is not falsity, it's just the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.50,1:30:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,In the absence of truth, there's no energy to her arm, and her arm goes weak.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.01,1:30:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what we're really getting is not true versus false, but true versus not true.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.37,1:30:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's a great addition to a great . . . that is correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.26,1:30:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.35,1:30:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what this means then, just as I was presented at age three or four, whatever it was, there's
Dialogue: 0,1:30:40.80,1:30:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,only that which is, there is only existence, there isn't such thing as nonexistence.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.24,1:30:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Nonexistence is not a possibility, a possibility would have to be a realizable reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:57.00,1:31:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Nonexistence by definition is not a realizable reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.51,1:31:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.51,1:31:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, there's an epistemologic realization, it would blow your head right off.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.11,1:31:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, the way to understand this then is, reality is what is, what is not is not.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.93,1:31:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point to fear what is not, because if it has no reality, why fear it, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.24,1:31:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,When we look at, if we run electricity through a wire, we say it's on, and then when there's
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.61,1:31:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,no electricity, we don't say, well, now there's offness there.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.48,1:31:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth electricity is either there, or it is not there.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:48.11,1:31:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,When electricity is not there, it doesn't mean that the opposite of electricity is
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.95,1:31:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,now there, something called offness, you understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.01,1:32:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This is very profound, this is the greater understanding that all of mankind has ever
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.69,1:32:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,reached.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.74,1:32:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It thinks.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.74,1:32:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just an offness.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:08.28,1:32:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.02,1:32:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what we discovered then with kinesiology is that truth makes you go strong, and you
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.73,1:32:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,go weak merely in the absence of truth, not in the presence of falsehood, because falsehood
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.11,1:32:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,does not exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.11,1:32:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is either present or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:29.06,1:32:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.03,1:32:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, suddenly I understood the first page in A Course in Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.75,1:32:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Only that truth is true, nothing else exists, therefore there is nothing to fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:47.38,1:32:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And I finally got it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.05,1:32:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.70,1:32:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,A long way around.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:54.70,1:32:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's presentation that the consciousness was at age three or four, existence versus
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.70,1:33:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,non-existence, because in that instant I feared that which is not, I feared non-existence,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.97,1:33:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,scared to death of non-existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.97,1:33:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But if I am, it could have been that.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.19,1:33:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It could have been that.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.19,1:33:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It could have been that I would not have been.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.19,1:33:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.19,1:33:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The hypothetical possibility of non-existence arose, and with it, fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.93,1:33:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there was the ego reborn in this lifetime, and its fear of non-existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.56,1:33:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that took care of me at age three or four, and that was the presentation of the dilemma
Dialogue: 0,1:33:37.72,1:33:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of this lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:38.72,1:33:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It took me another, what, seventy years to do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:44.15,1:33:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:45.15,1:33:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.15,1:33:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a very profound, it was a presentation, and it was non-verbal, and there was no way
Dialogue: 0,1:33:54.98,1:33:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to speak of it to anyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:58.03,1:34:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And nothing else of any particular interest happened, except that I was not particularly
Dialogue: 0,1:34:02.03,1:34:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,physical.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:03.03,1:34:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I wasn't much into physicality, I like nature, but wrestling and stickball and sticking
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.19,1:34:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,greasy fingernails in people's eyes was not my idea of fun.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:12.83,1:34:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, other boys sort of enjoyed this physical adversarial kind of amusement, which I was
Dialogue: 0,1:34:18.90,1:34:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,always very boring.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.90,1:34:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But, other than that, I seemed like a normal boy, and I used to say I graduated at the
Dialogue: 0,1:34:25.54,1:34:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,top of my class in kindergarten.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:26.54,1:34:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I got a straight A in crayons.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.54,1:34:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I made that joke up.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.54,1:34:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's stupid.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.54,1:34:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, you don't want to sound too serious or anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.54,1:34:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway, in teenage, I did have a problem in that I'd be sitting in class, and in the
Dialogue: 0,1:34:31.54,1:34:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,minute if I started to think about who I was, think of I.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.54,1:34:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of I.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.08,1:34:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of I.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.08,1:34:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of I.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:36.08,1:34:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of I.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.08,1:34:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of I.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.87,1:34:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of I.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.87,1:34:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of I.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:41.87,1:34:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of I.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.87,1:34:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of I.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.87,1:34:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of I.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.87,1:34:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of I.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.87,1:34:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of I.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:46.87,1:34:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of I.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.87,1:34:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of I.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:48.87,1:34:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of I.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.87,1:34:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of I.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.87,1:34:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of I.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:51.87,1:34:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of I.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.97,1:34:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The thought of I, the self would begin, that which the world calls the self, would begin
Dialogue: 0,1:34:58.06,1:34:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to dissolve.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.06,1:35:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If there was the self, I would lose track of an individual, discrete entity called I,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:04.06,1:35:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,which the world addresses David all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:08.22,1:35:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I assume that's his name, because that's what they kept calling him then.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:12.31,1:35:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And, this would sort of tend to dissolve.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.31,1:35:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, one time I had a paper wrote when I was about 12 or 14.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.41,1:35:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I wrote about this in the back of the book, Power Versus Self.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.41,1:35:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a note about the author at the end.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:25.41,1:35:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they probably wanted to know who he is, so I put it in the back.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.41,1:35:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, later people said, you should put that at the front.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.63,1:35:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, anyway, I put it in the back.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:33.66,1:35:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, about 12 or 14, somewhere in that, I had this paper wrote, and in the middle
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.66,1:35:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,of a blizzard, it was very dark and I got lost in this blizzard, it was many miles from
Dialogue: 0,1:35:42.66,1:35:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,home, and I was free, you know, I actually sort of freed from death, and so I dug into
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.94,1:35:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,a big snowbank there in Wisconsin.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.94,1:35:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,In Wisconsin, the snow is very high.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.94,1:35:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I dug into a big snowbank there, a big one.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:53.01,1:35:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and the snow was very high on Saturday night, 12 feet high or 15 feet high.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.44,1:36:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, I dug through the, into the snow and got into this hole out of the wind.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.92,1:36:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the wind was fierce.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:05.54,1:36:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It was about 20 blow or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.64,1:36:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And I snuggled in there, and very soon, very quickly,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:13.66,1:36:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,a profound sense of relaxation and peace came on me.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.98,1:36:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It was really incredible.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:18.16,1:36:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the infinite, exquisite sensation of gentleness.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:25.46,1:36:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like exquisite love just took me over in this golden presence.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:30.34,1:36:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And to this day, I wish I'd stayed there anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.98,1:36:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, all time disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:40.76,1:36:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That which, this golden, infinite presence of exquisite love,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.86,1:36:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,melting, just melted away any personal.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:50.54,1:36:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:50.62,1:36:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no self, which dissolved.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:52.04,1:36:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There wasn't any personal self.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.94,1:36:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,There was just this infinite presence.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:58.46,1:37:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Not different than that which I am.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:01.20,1:37:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And I saw that which I am is before all universes
Dialogue: 0,1:37:06.67,1:37:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and will exist long after all universes have come and gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:11.70,1:37:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond all time, beyond all dimension, beyond all universes, beyond all description.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:19.64,1:37:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,This infinite presence.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:21.12,1:37:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there I stayed for some eons or so.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:25.62,1:37:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And the next thing I knew, my father was shaking my knee to come on our Model A Ford,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:31.38,1:37:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,29 Model A Ford, and located the body there in the hole and retraced the paper route.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:37.64,1:37:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, anyway, he was quite shaken by all this.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:40.96,1:37:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, father reaches in and grabs the knee.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:43.94,1:37:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And I really was extremely reluctant to resume this physicality.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:50.52,1:37:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But I got that he believes in death.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:53.81,1:37:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I could see that he would think that if this body,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:57.65,1:38:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,if this body didn't start to move again, that it was dead, and that he, that I had died.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:03.37,1:38:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And this would bring profound grief.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:07.41,1:38:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's the idea that it's absurd, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:12.41,1:38:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But anyway, in his state, it seemed like a reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:16.65,1:38:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,In my state, it was an absurdity.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:18.29,1:38:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Absurdity.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:18.89,1:38:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But I saw that he couldn't see my state.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:20.71,1:38:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for the sake of love, then, I re-energized this body.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:26.46,1:38:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was probably a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:29.26,1:38:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this happened on several occasions throughout my life.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:32.96,1:38:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this happened on several occasions throughout my life.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.04,1:38:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this happened on several occasions throughout my life.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.32,1:38:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it happened another time under similar conditions.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:36.76,1:38:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was doing rebirthing, and the breathing stopped.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:39.76,1:38:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And the same space, I went back into being that way, which I am.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:45.55,1:38:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And there was no necessity to breathe again.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:49.17,1:38:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't see any reason to breathe.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:50.71,1:38:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But I didn't seem to need to breathe.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.05,1:38:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't interested in breathing.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:53.92,1:38:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But the rebirther took quite a concerned interest in whether I breathed or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:58.44,1:38:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Laughter
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.04,1:39:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He was teaching me this.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:04.09,1:39:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,He was teaching me this technique, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:05.72,1:39:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And anyway, I loved him.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:07.84,1:39:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So, telepathically, I'm getting from him, breathe, Dave, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:11.96,1:39:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And I got his position.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.36,1:39:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I was his first patient, his first rebirther.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:17.66,1:39:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a rebirther.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:19.68,1:39:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He had just come back from the place that grew green pig vegetables there by the sea.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.28,1:39:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget where.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:29.28,1:39:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Benhorn, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:29.96,1:39:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he had taken the course of miracles to Benhorn.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:32.02,1:39:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He had taken the course of miracles.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:34.35,1:39:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He was now into rebirthing.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:36.51,1:39:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Dave, I've got to show you this.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:37.49,1:39:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He takes me on this rebirthing trip.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.22,1:39:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.58,1:39:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, there was no desire.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:42.72,1:39:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And I could see the same thing happening all over again.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:44.88,1:39:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Here I am in this incredible space.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:46.88,1:39:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's this idiot thinking that I'm going to die if I don't breathe again.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:51.18,1:39:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And I see that the whole world is going to believe, believe that he did.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:55.28,1:39:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Dave died.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:56.20,1:39:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So, and it's going to be on his head.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:58.16,1:40:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So, he's looking at me, you know, projecting the position I'm going to leave him if I don't breathe again.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:06.50,1:40:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:08.62,1:40:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:09.55,1:40:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So, again, I made the same fatal mistake.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:12.91,1:40:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Laughter
Dialogue: 0,1:40:13.27,1:40:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And out of love resumed it.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:17.95,1:40:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And, but then the more interesting things that happened were perhaps in spiritual work, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:23.93,1:40:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I would belong to the first Zen Institute.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:25.93,1:40:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was a psychiatric consultant to the Zen monastery and the Episcopal Diocese and the Catholic Diocese and the Catholic nuns.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:40.07,1:40:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And so my spiritual experience was sort of used in a way to differentiate.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:45.51,1:40:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, abnormal religious states from legitimate states.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:52.19,1:40:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And, uh, that was before we had a kinesiology or any way to test such things.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:57.84,1:41:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, at one time I, um, was in a profound state of illness.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:02.62,1:41:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And, uh, I went into this profound state of illness.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:06.53,1:41:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, one time I went out of body.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:08.69,1:41:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I might as well relate all these experiences.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:10.35,1:41:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a difference between near death and out of body.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:13.37,1:41:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And I just want to make that clear.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:14.69,1:41:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Near, near death was the golden, uh, exquisite.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:17.69,1:41:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,When you calibrate the low.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.15,1:41:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness of that, uh, uh, field of energy, uh, you get it's quite a high, high field.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:27.37,1:41:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And, uh, the person's consciousness is not the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:31.19,1:41:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Once, a near death experience, you're different.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:34.19,1:41:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, you see the fear of death disappears altogether.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:37.13,1:41:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I never had the fear of death from age 12 on.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:40.38,1:41:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The fear of death disappears and very often their whole life is somewhat transformed.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:45.58,1:41:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of body is, is different.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:47.04,1:41:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of body, uh, happened one time when I was very physically sick.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:50.08,1:41:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And, uh, suddenly found myself in mid-air, six feet over this physical body, looking down at the bed, and there was Dave in this bed.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:56.90,1:42:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, he was a mess, I'll tell ya.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:00.60,1:42:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I looked at him, I thought, God, he should be leaving this world soon.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:03.60,1:42:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And, uh, but this was totally different.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:06.98,1:42:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no golden light.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:08.18,1:42:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no exquisite presence.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:09.86,1:42:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But there was, um, weightlessness and, uh, thought, feeling, uh, and, uh, capacity to see and hear went with, uh, spirit body.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:20.27,1:42:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Went with the etheric.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:20.93,1:42:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Here I am up in space, and I look, here's this body, it's almost exactly like this one, except it's, uh, almost like invisible.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:27.43,1:42:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see right, right through it, it had no weight.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.43,1:42:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And a slight thought would move it anywhere in space, it was like weightless.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:33.62,1:42:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And I remember looking down and seeing the physical body laying in the bed, and, uh, later that was interesting because I realized that, uh,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:42.90,1:42:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the quality of hearing, thinking, feeling, et cetera, goes with the etheric body.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:48.73,1:42:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't go with the physical body.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:50.83,1:42:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And the illusion is, uh,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:53.33,1:42:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's happening through the physical body.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:55.33,1:42:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you can hear without the body's ears, and you can see without the body's eyes.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:58.83,1:43:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they were laying there in the bed, and I was up there seeing and hearing.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:01.83,1:43:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway, if you calibrate the level of consciousness of the entity before and after this experience, it's the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:08.62,1:43:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So the difference between out-of-body is that you're the same person, it's just that your etheric and physical are separated.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:14.74,1:43:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And the near-death is quite a different, more profound, transformative experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:20.97,1:43:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, then, uh,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:25.50,1:43:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to clarify, because I saw a TV documentary on it,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:28.50,1:43:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and it confused the two states,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:30.50,1:43:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,treated near-death and out-of-body as though they were the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:33.50,1:43:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And they're quite a bit different, quite a bit different.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:36.50,1:43:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's, let's calibrate, what was the level of, uh, snowbank experience, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:40.98,1:43:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we have permission to calibrate that resist?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:44.34,1:43:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It was over 600 resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:46.37,1:43:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It was over 700 resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:48.37,1:43:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It was 750 resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:49.37,1:43:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It was 800 resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:50.37,1:43:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It was 900 resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:52.37,1:43:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It was over 900 resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:53.37,1:43:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my God.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:54.37,1:43:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:55.72,1:43:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, uh,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:56.72,1:43:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,um,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:58.23,1:44:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the Divine Presence was actually the Divine Presence,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:00.23,1:44:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and, uh,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:02.33,1:44:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I always thought it was God, but didn't want to say anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:07.33,1:44:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,See, you can calibrate where, what was that experience,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:10.33,1:44:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that you had or other people had.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:13.33,1:44:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you can go back through history, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:15.33,1:44:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the spiritual experiences of saints and various people.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:18.33,1:44:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What's real, what's not real.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:19.33,1:44:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the level of calibration of that?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:21.33,1:44:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you begin to get a feeling for the entire spiritual dimension
Dialogue: 0,1:44:26.42,1:44:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of what's real, and where does it fit into the overall reality,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:29.42,1:44:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and many supposed dilemmas result in self.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:34.42,1:44:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, at the bottom, uh, then, uh, at a certain age,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:39.54,1:44:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I suddenly became, well, I was brought up Episcopal,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:41.54,1:44:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was very religious, and, uh, I was a boy soprano,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:46.41,1:44:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, boy soprano with, uh, a choir and a full orchestra
Dialogue: 0,1:44:51.82,1:44:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and a cathedral, and I sang the Obligato to Panis Angelicus.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:56.02,1:44:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it brought tears to the eyes of me
Dialogue: 0,1:44:58.02,1:45:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and everybody in the room.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:00.02,1:45:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a soprano boy, Obligato, with his voice coming out of
Dialogue: 0,1:45:03.02,1:45:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know where.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:05.02,1:45:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And, uh, this whole floor, I mean, it was really a great moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:09.02,1:45:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So religion, you know, used to just lift me up,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:12.02,1:45:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the sheer aesthetics of it, the sheer beauty of it,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:14.02,1:45:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the sheer beauty and joy of the cathedral,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:17.02,1:45:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, and the entire pageantry of it, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:20.02,1:45:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,it's an exquisite experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:22.75,1:45:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, well, anyway, so, then one time,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:27.01,1:45:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I was looking at, uh, the suffering of man,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:29.01,1:45:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:30.01,1:45:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, all of a sudden, um, I came into the awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.86,1:45:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,of the totality of the suffering of all of mankind,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:42.37,1:45:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,like I saw all of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:44.37,1:45:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It was beyond all dimension, all capacity to describe.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:49.30,1:45:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The totality of the suffering of mankind throughout all of time
Dialogue: 0,1:45:52.49,1:45:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,was so profound that in that instant I became an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:57.26,1:46:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, um, any God that could allow this possibility
Dialogue: 0,1:46:02.80,1:46:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,could not be God to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:03.96,1:46:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the fire.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:05.15,1:46:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a profound atheist.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:06.47,1:46:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,A dedicated atheist.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:08.50,1:46:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a fool around atheists.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:10.66,1:46:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I was as serious about atheism as I had been about religion, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:15.66,1:46:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And I went to a Jesuit university.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:18.70,1:46:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Here I am with this profound atheist at a Jesuit university.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:21.70,1:46:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm getting straight A in theology and Thomas Aquinas
Dialogue: 0,1:46:24.70,1:46:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and all this.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:27.95,1:46:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And in myself, I'm an atheist, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:29.95,1:46:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway, uh, that was the position I took.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:36.04,1:46:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,One that a great part of mankind takes.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:38.04,1:46:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand it because I experienced the very essence of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:43.29,1:46:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Without understanding karma, without understanding the true nature of God,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:47.29,1:46:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,anybody with any brain really ought to be an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:50.29,1:46:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think God is the cause of all that occurs in this universe, in this world,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:56.41,1:47:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and you still believe in him, then you must be pretty depraved.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:01.75,1:47:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the honest arguments for the existence of God
Dialogue: 0,1:47:05.75,1:47:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,have made atheists and many an honest man.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:07.75,1:47:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was one of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:08.75,1:47:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,How could an all-merciful, all-loving, all-beneficial, beneficial God
Dialogue: 0,1:47:18.88,1:47:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,allow that degree of negativity and suffering of all mankind?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:23.91,1:47:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And at that point, I became an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:28.18,1:47:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was a very serious atheist, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:30.18,1:47:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I really took it seriously.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:32.79,1:47:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I loved religious discussions and theological discussions, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:35.79,1:47:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was really good at it, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:37.79,1:47:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I could really, like, take a snack, take that.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:40.79,1:47:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I was really good at it.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:42.79,1:47:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway, I was out to destroy the false gods.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:45.79,1:47:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't realize they were false gods.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:48.79,1:47:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was the false concept, conceptions of God,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:51.79,1:47:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that I had taken issue with.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:54.98,1:47:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And as it turned out, certainly so.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:57.98,1:48:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, the misconceptions of God is what anybody
Dialogue: 0,1:48:02.14,1:48:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,with any real profound spiritual sense cannot buy,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:06.14,1:48:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,unless there's profound negative depictions of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:09.30,1:48:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway, I was a profound atheist.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:12.82,1:48:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And after some years went by,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:14.82,1:48:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I then developed some other illnesses.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:16.82,1:48:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And at one time, I hit a state of profound spiritual blackness,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:24.36,1:48:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,profound depth, spiritual depths.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:27.58,1:48:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, the pits of hell, in a way.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:30.90,1:48:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Pits of hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:32.16,1:48:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Despair and blackness beyond all description.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:35.16,1:48:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this black despair, it was really sort of the pits of hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:41.25,1:48:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the upper parts of hell are torture and the devil
Dialogue: 0,1:48:45.25,1:48:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and all that kind of stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:46.25,1:48:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But those are just the upper realms.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:49.02,1:48:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And the bottom realms are those of profound spiritual desolation,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:54.72,1:48:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,cut off from all light, you might say.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:58.46,1:49:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that state, here I'm an atheist, a devoted atheist,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:04.19,1:49:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, and I thought, I'm probably going to die.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:07.19,1:49:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, I'm about to die.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:09.80,1:49:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought, before I do, I mean, what if I'm wrong?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:15.80,1:49:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In a couple of minutes, this could be tacky.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:17.80,1:49:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you could be on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:19.80,1:49:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:21.80,1:49:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,A few errors we ought to look into here, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:24.90,1:49:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, well, if there is a God, I ask him to help me.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:30.44,1:49:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, I don't remember anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:32.44,1:49:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:34.63,1:49:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I came to, when I came to some days later,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:38.63,1:49:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,or whenever it was, I don't know,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:40.98,1:49:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,everything had been transformed.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:42.98,1:49:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All of existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:43.98,1:49:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,My experience of existence, of my own existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:47.94,1:49:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything was totally transformed.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:49.94,1:49:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only a brilliant...
Dialogue: 0,1:49:51.94,1:49:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The divinity of all things shines forth equally
Dialogue: 0,1:49:56.39,1:49:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,as the essence of all things being what they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:59.39,1:50:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The exquisite beauty of the infinite presence is overwhelming.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:03.39,1:50:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And the mind, what the world calls the mind, it stopped.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:07.35,1:50:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,No thought, no thought possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:09.35,1:50:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind still doesn't think.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:11.48,1:50:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't think at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:12.48,1:50:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This morning it wasn't thinking about anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:14.48,1:50:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It was wandering around, I don't know what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:16.48,1:50:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the mind just came to a stunning stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:19.61,1:50:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And nor would there be any, even the slightest,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:22.61,1:50:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,possibility of having a thought in that presence.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:27.67,1:50:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The presence is of such infinite power.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:30.67,1:50:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Power is so infinite.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:34.08,1:50:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like the intrinsic power that holds everything together.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:40.08,1:50:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything that holds this room together.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:42.08,1:50:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Power.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:43.08,1:50:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And this infinite power is also exquisitely gentle.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:47.43,1:50:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And closer, closer than what one thinks of as one's self.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:52.72,1:50:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What you think of as yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:54.98,1:50:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Is really quite distant from what you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:56.98,1:51:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you, the realization of the self with a capital S
Dialogue: 0,1:51:00.98,1:51:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is more profoundly one's home.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:03.98,1:51:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The source of one's existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:05.98,1:51:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Where one really lives.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:08.07,1:51:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Than what had been thought of as one's self.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:11.07,1:51:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So this infinite presence then,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:15.42,1:51:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,which took the place of all that had prior existence,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:19.48,1:51:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,John Dowdall thought.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:21.48,1:51:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,John Dowdall thought of an individual separate self,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:24.48,1:51:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,or an I.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:25.48,1:51:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The world called data on earth to figure out what they were talking about at the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:31.30,1:51:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,When it first happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:33.72,1:51:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There was quite a difficulty in pronouns.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:35.72,1:51:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And the people were always talking to this body.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:37.72,1:51:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And it would mystify me.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:38.72,1:51:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Why the hell are they talking to that body?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:39.72,1:51:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not even there.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:40.72,1:51:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, why are they?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:42.72,1:51:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I realized that they assumed that this body is me.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:44.72,1:51:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh wow, I got that.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:47.20,1:51:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was quite a while, some years in fact,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:50.20,1:51:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that I could figure out how to really function within the world again.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:54.20,1:51:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the world didn't, the world, the mind didn't say anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:58.20,1:52:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,People spoke with things that seemed to have no reality or relevance whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:04.58,1:52:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's a split second of translation.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:11.29,1:52:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I see the person's mouth speaking.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:13.29,1:52:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The words impinge on the ear, but they don't have any meaning.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:17.61,1:52:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Holy Spirit translates that into an understanding of what is being said.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:22.61,1:52:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Or I'll say to somebody, what are they saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:25.64,1:52:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And that gives me the moment I need.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:27.64,1:52:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,To interpret what is happening within the world of form.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:35.86,1:52:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So there was some years of trying to live within the world of form.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:39.98,1:52:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how I left New York City and the big practice I had there and all.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:44.30,1:52:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And I went out to a small town.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:46.30,1:52:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And for about ten years I had nothing to do with the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:49.34,1:52:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I just got used to the state and how to regain functioning within it.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:53.34,1:52:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So that was quite a remarkable thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:58.42,1:53:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there were various sensations along the way.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:00.42,1:53:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,In the eye of the eye, I think I wrote about them.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:03.55,1:53:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,People do a lot of spiritual work.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:05.55,1:53:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,They really need others to compare their experience with.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:08.55,1:53:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there isn't all that many people out there to talk to about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:11.55,1:53:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought, well, maybe a lot of the things I consider irrelevant maybe are not irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:16.55,1:53:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I should write about them.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:17.55,1:53:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I should...
Dialogue: 0,1:53:19.68,1:53:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a period when the kundalini energy was running up my spine.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:22.68,1:53:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It was exquisite.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:23.68,1:53:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it wasn't happening to anybody else.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:25.68,1:53:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I could run around and say, hey, there's something running up your spine.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:27.68,1:53:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It feels exquisite, like a little great orgasm going on.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:29.68,1:53:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,All the time in your brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:31.68,1:53:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, Doc, you really tipped over, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:35.68,1:53:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Seen too many crazies, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:38.68,1:53:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, yeah, it was exquisite energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:41.68,1:53:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I forget what I was doing at the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:43.68,1:53:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But anyway, some spiritual practice.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:45.68,1:53:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It can happen to almost any spiritual practice.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:48.74,1:53:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You do the Course in Miracles and you have all kinds of incredible experiences.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:51.74,1:53:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, this energy is running up the spine and up my back.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:56.74,1:53:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's pouring into my brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:58.74,1:54:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's exquisite, exquisite all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:01.74,1:54:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Exquisitely pleasurable.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:04.35,1:54:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Just, oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:05.35,1:54:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I would think of the left side of my brain, it would sort of like go into the left side of the brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:10.51,1:54:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If I think of the right side of the brain, it would go into the right side of the brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:13.51,1:54:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:14.51,1:54:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And so this exquisite energy went on for years.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:18.51,1:54:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it would come down this way and sort of go out through the heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:22.86,1:54:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'd be driving somewhere and all of a sudden this energy would pour out down the road or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:29.25,1:54:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And a very exquisite sensation.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:32.25,1:54:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'd say, well, I don't know what.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:35.25,1:54:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And this energy would go down the highway some miles ahead of where I was.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:40.25,1:54:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I turned the bend, there was an accident.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:43.28,1:54:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The car is upside down and the wheels are still turning.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:46.28,1:54:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And this energy is pouring into the car.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:48.28,1:54:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And I got that there was no need to stop physically.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:53.72,1:54:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no need for physical assistance on my part.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:56.72,1:54:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,This energy seemed to be handling everything that needed to be handled.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:59.72,1:55:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And then as I go down the road, it stopped again.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:03.91,1:55:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm going down the highway again.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:06.91,1:55:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,All of a sudden it started again.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:09.04,1:55:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:10.04,1:55:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going around the next bend a couple of miles ahead.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:13.04,1:55:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Exquisite.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:14.04,1:55:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Just pouring out into this like a radiance.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:17.04,1:55:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And I come around the bend and there, my God, there's another accident.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:21.65,1:55:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This time the emergency vehicles are on the way.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:25.65,1:55:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And the lights are flashing.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:27.65,1:55:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They're coming down the highway.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:28.65,1:55:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And this energy poured into the car.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:29.65,1:55:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And this energy poured into the people in that wreck.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:32.65,1:55:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And did the same thing again.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:34.81,1:55:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So this peculiar phenomena would occur.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:37.81,1:55:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And various paranormal, what the world calls paranormal phenomena would happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:44.38,1:55:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Sanskrit, it's called the various cities.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:47.38,1:55:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the S-I-B-D-H-I-S.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:49.38,1:55:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're warned not to get trapped by them or enamored of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:53.82,1:55:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, they happen as a result of the presence.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:58.69,1:56:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,They have nothing to do with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:00.69,1:56:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This divine presence did all these things.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:02.69,1:56:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This presence would answer people's questions.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:05.69,1:56:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It would phrase responses that the body would verbalize to the person's question.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:13.78,1:56:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And it would be amazing, I think.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:15.78,1:56:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, wow, that's pretty neat.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:17.78,1:56:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there was clairvoyance.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:22.84,1:56:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There was this envision.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:25.84,1:56:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There was, what do you call it, psychometry.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:27.84,1:56:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Where you pick up something, you know, whose book this is.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:30.84,1:56:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can see who that person is.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:32.84,1:56:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And you've got everything about that person.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:35.35,1:56:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Just from touching it.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:36.35,1:56:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And that would occur automatically.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:38.35,1:56:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And all those things came and went.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:40.35,1:56:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, they would last for, oh, four or five years.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:45.28,1:56:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Electronic things would fix themselves.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:48.47,1:56:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And somebody would come over to repair a 100-amp amplifier.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:54.53,1:56:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'd look at it and I'd say, I don't know, it looks okay to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:59.23,1:57:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And instantly the thing would go off.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:01.23,1:57:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And the guy looks at it and he says, whoa.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:03.23,1:57:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you do there?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:05.23,1:57:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, I didn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:06.23,1:57:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, there's some kind of presence that does these things.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:09.55,1:57:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, it all started from reading The Chorus of Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:12.55,1:57:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, gee, I want that book.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:15.55,1:57:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I had exactly one copy left, so I gave it to him.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:19.55,1:57:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, well, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:20.55,1:57:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And he left and tears me to the surface for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:24.55,1:57:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And he only came over to get The Chorus of Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:26.55,1:57:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why, you know, God sent him over.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:29.90,1:57:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He came over to get The Chorus of Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:31.90,1:57:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I never saw him again.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:32.90,1:57:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But those things were, they lasted for, I don't know, five or six years, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:38.80,1:57:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Some years it was, I hadn't even been in the same, that state before.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:42.86,1:57:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And people would say, we're running out of gas.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:44.86,1:57:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'd say, oh, there's a Saccone station a mile or two down the road.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:51.47,1:57:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I could see it in my mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:52.47,1:57:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all exactly where it is, you know, around the trees there.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:55.47,1:57:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And so this phenomenon would occur.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:57.54,1:57:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So, yes, the paranormal does have a certain reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:59.54,1:58:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah, it does exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:01.54,1:58:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And what we notice about Scripture is it's going to exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:03.54,1:58:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But what we don't notice about Scripture is that Scripture says, it doesn't say the supernatural doesn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:07.54,1:58:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It just says, don't go there.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:09.54,1:58:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't go there.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:10.54,1:58:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:11.54,1:58:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you get caught in the astral realms, that's why.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:13.54,1:58:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You get caught in the astral realms.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:15.57,1:58:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And so much of what people think is spiritual, especially in New Age groups,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:19.57,1:58:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that don't have being on the earth, is, you know, endless preoccupation with astral realms.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:27.69,1:58:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,There are endless astral realms.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:29.69,1:58:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,There are heavens upon heavens, and there's hierarchies,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:32.69,1:58:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's masters and gurus,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:34.72,1:58:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and followers,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:35.72,1:58:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and mystical carryings on,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:38.88,1:58:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and people with the colored rays,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:40.88,1:58:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and people with the light beams,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:41.88,1:58:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and people with the...
Dialogue: 0,1:58:45.30,1:58:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, the world's full of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:47.30,1:58:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So the astral domains is not the same as the spiritual reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:52.30,1:58:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So I want to make that clear,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:54.42,1:59:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,because a lot of seekers get pulled into early astral domains.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:01.64,1:59:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're going to listen to somebody channeling master so-and-so,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:05.64,1:59:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you better calibrate the energy of master so-and-so on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:08.64,1:59:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Very, very good.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:10.38,1:59:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Because very often master so-and-so is in the control,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:13.38,1:59:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in the control,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:14.38,1:59:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and calibrates less than 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:16.38,1:59:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,His only desire is to control people out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:19.38,1:59:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got them sitting out there waiting for UFOs to land and save them in the middle of the desert
Dialogue: 0,1:59:23.38,1:59:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and all kinds of crazy crap.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:27.38,1:59:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And these are just demons that get a kick out of scaring people,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:30.38,1:59:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,especially if they think they have some kind of...
Dialogue: 0,1:59:32.38,1:59:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They're on some spiritual trick, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:34.38,1:59:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you're a demon,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:35.38,1:59:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't you just love to twist people's noses around a spiritual trick
Dialogue: 0,1:59:38.38,1:59:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and say,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:39.38,1:59:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,take that,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:40.38,1:59:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,sit out in the middle of the desert and starve to death?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:42.38,1:59:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They do, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:43.38,1:59:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll go out in the desert and wait for God to show up.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:46.89,1:59:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,All kinds of strange things.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:47.89,1:59:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So one reason to calibrate things is
Dialogue: 0,1:59:51.46,1:59:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not that a channeled teaching is necessarily negative.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:57.50,1:59:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It may well be positive.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:59.50,2:00:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You should know who is it,
Dialogue: 0,2:00:00.50,2:00:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, what is the level of truth of the consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,2:00:03.50,2:00:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,because many people go into,
Dialogue: 0,2:00:04.50,2:00:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,ooh, ah, it's all master.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:06.50,2:00:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Baba, ding dong.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:08.50,2:00:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know, you go,
Dialogue: 0,2:00:09.50,2:00:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the energy of Master Ding Dong?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:11.50,2:00:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to think it was very Chinese Baba right now.
